2015 @-@ 2018 Deputy Secretary of the Party Committee , China Institute of Engineering and Physics
Vice Governor and Member of Party Group , Guangdong Provincial Government , September 2018
According to the British media , Lieutenant General William Moran , Vice Navy Operations Secretary of the United States , said that even as the United States Navy is revitalizing its forces to deal with an increasingly worrisome Russia on both sides of the Atlantic , the United States continues to focus its navy on the Asia @-@ Pacific region -- the Pentagon extends the region to include the Indian Ocean @ -@ Asia @ -@ -Pacific .
According to a September 24 report from the United Kingdom &apos;s Jane &apos;s Defense Weekly website , the United States listed China and Russia as strategic competitors in a new defense strategy released earlier this year .
Since then , the United States Navy has resumed its Second Fleet in order to confront Russia &apos;s activities more directly .
he report said that these moves raised some questions and concerns among allies and analysts , who feared that the US Navy might distance itself from the Asia @-@ Pacific rebalancing strategy that marked the Obama administration .
But Admiral Moran said that the US Navy &apos;s focus remained on the Western Pacific .
At the round @-@ table discussion entitled &quot; Responding to the challenges of the high seas , &quot; hosted by the National Asian Research Agency of the United States in Washington , D.C. , on 24 January 2018 , he said that there had been no major changes for us .
Moran said : The emphasis is still on rebalancing , shifting the center of gravity , or whatever you want to describe it .
He acknowledged , however , that the United States was closely linked to Europe .
He said , &quot; We will continue to focus on growth on the West Coast and balance what we can do . &quot;
Though Moran points out that overall policy toward Russia falls within the purview of the US Secretary of Defense , he warns that Russians may face demographic and economic challenges , but history has shown that if we clash with them , they will be hard @-@ line .
Admiral Moran said that as part of America &apos;s renewed campaign against Russia , China , and other competitors , the US Navy is dynamically deploying its troops into a new mode of combat , which will help the adversaries to be unprepared about where the US aircraft carrier battle groups or other assets will be deployed at any particular time and location .
He said : &quot; We navy and marines support it -- the concept of unpredictability of combat , do not appear in the same place time and again , almost like issuing banners -- this is our approach . &quot;
According to the report , the first attempt to try this new approach was made by the aircraft carrier battle group , the early deployment of which included working visits to ports and patrolling areas that normally pass only .
Moran said that the US Navy is currently working to ensure that allies know that these warships will continue to patrol traditional areas , and is also addressing logistical and family liaison issues for the new deployment process .
Lieutenant General Michael Nunnan , the Commander of the Royal Australian Navy , also spoke at the event , saying that the Australian army could cooperate seamlessly with the United States aircraft carrier battle group .
He said that the situation would continue as the Royal Australian Navy planned to purchase an additional nine frigates equipped with combat systems .
Starting from October 5 , many airlines have increased or resumed the fuel surcharge . Additional money will be needed next Friday for the aircraft to travel
Yesterday , Xiangpeng Airlines , Okay Airlines and other airlines announced to the public that , starting from October 5 , 2018 ( the date of ticketing ) , the fuel surcharge for domestic airlines will be 20 Yuan per passenger for less than 800 kilometers , and 30 Yuan per passenger for more than 800 kilometers .
Xiangpeng Airlines , Okay Airlines and others announced that , starting at zero on October 5 , 2018 ( date of ticketing ) , the standard for charging fuel surcharges for domestic routes below 800 kilometers ( including ) increased from 10 yuan per person to 20 yuan per person , and the standard for charging fuel surcharges for domestic routes above 800 kilometers increased from 10 yuan per passenger per person to 30 yuan per person .
Children , military and police have a disability of 10 yuan per person ; babies continue to be exempted .
ccording to the person responsible for the travel ticket , the airline has already indicated in the notification that the fuel surcharge will be collected on the basis of the date of the original ticket issuance and that the fuel surcharge will not be refunded when the passenger ticket is exchanged .
This means that domestic airline passenger tickets issued before 5 October do not have to pay the fuel surcharge according to the new standard if they are to be changed to or including 5 October .
Since June 5 , 2018 , many airlines including China National , China Eastern , China Sea , Shanghai Aviation , Chunqiu Aviation , Shenzhen Aviation , West Aviation , and Okay Airways have resumed collecting surcharges for fuel from domestic airlines that have been cancelled for three years , at a standard rate of 10 yuan per person .
This time , Xiangpeng Airlines and Okay Airlines took the lead in announcing an increase in the fuel surcharge . As of the time the reporter issued his report , he had not seen any news of the four major airlines in China announcing a follow @-@ up adjustment .
It is also known that the Hong Kong Civil Aviation Authority provides that airlines may decide whether to charge fuel surcharges at their own discretion from November .
At the earliest , on 27 September , it was announced that the fuel surcharge would begin on 2 November .
According to the China @-@ Thailand aviation website , airfares issued or reissued by all China @-@ Thailand and China @-@ Thailand Harlong on or after 2 November will include fuel surcharges for long @-@ distance flights to and from Hong Kong and the south @-@ west Pacific , North America , Europe , the Middle East and India , and Africa , at a fuel surcharge of 652 yuan , and 146 yuan for short @-@ distance flights .
Costs apply to all ticket types , calculated on the basis of each flight segment , and include quotations for airfares from all direct sales channels in Kuwait and Thailand .
On the eve of the sixty @-@ ninth anniversary of the founding of the People &apos;s Republic of China , the Premier of the State Council of China , Li Keqiang , met in the Great Hall of the People &apos;s Assembly on the afternoon of the 30th with the new ambassadors of 29 countries and regions to China .
Li Keqiang talked with all the ambassadors accredited to China , shaking hands one by one .
Li Keqiang welcomed the envoys to China and asked them to convey their sincere greetings and best wishes to the leaders and peoples of the countries concerned and to the leaders of the institutions concerned .
Li Keqiang positively assessed China &apos;s good relations with various countries and regions . He stressed China &apos;s commitment to enhancing bilateral political trust , deepening practical cooperation , and strengthening coordination and cooperation in international and regional affairs . He hoped that the fans would walk more and see more and make a new positive contribution to the development of China &apos;s relations with their respective countries and regions in new positions .
The Chinese Government stands ready to facilitate and support them in the performance of their duties .
Li Keqiang pointed out that China is persisting on the path of peaceful development and is firmly committed to economic globalization .
This year marks the fortieth anniversary of China &apos;s reform and opening up . As the world &apos;s largest developing country , we are ready to work with all countries in further expanding the opening up .
In the context of the rise of protectionism and unilateralism , we stand ready to continue to work with all parties to consolidate and strengthen partnerships based on the principles of mutual respect , equality and mutual benefit , to promote docking development strategies , to promote cooperation on the one side and on the other , to work together to defend multilateralism and free trade , to build an open world economy and to give new impetus to the stable and balanced development of the world economy .
All countries and institutions in China warmly congratulated the People &apos;s Republic of China on its sixty @-@ ninth anniversary , conveyed the greetings of the leaders of their respective countries and institutions to the leaders and people of China , and expressed their strong development achievements and their conviction that further deepening reform and opening @-@ up in the future would bring more development opportunities to the world .
We are willing to play a positive role in promoting friendly cooperation between our respective countries and regions and China in order to better realize mutual benefits and win @-@ win results .
Subsequently , at the invitation of Li Keqiang , national envoys and agencies to China attended the National Day reception .
State Councillor and Minister for Foreign Affairs Wang Yi attended the event .
