In May 2016 , in Tokyo , Japan , a man walked through Myitsu Hong Kong &apos;s headquarters .
hong said that the US grain sector under the banner of the trade war , Gao Hong , had suspended financial transactions in agriculture .
Earlier , some Japanese heavy equipment manufacturers , telecom companies and others had warned of the impact of trade friction between China and the United States when they released the latest performance . Now , these Japanese trading houses have joined the ranks .
The US and China are imposing tariffs on hundreds of billions of dollars of each other &apos;s goods , and US President Donald Trump has threatened to extend the tax to more than $ 500 billion of Chinese goods lost to the US if the dispute is not resolved .
According to Tsuyoshi Hachimura , the commercial treasurer of Ifuju , next year &apos;s trade dispute is likely to have a greater impact on the Chinese economy .
Ito Tzhong Commercial and Thai Bbee Group invested $ 10 billion in China in 2015 , gaining a 20 % stake in it .
Hachimura states that Ifuju Tizhong Commercial lost 143.3 billion yen ( USD 1.3 billion ) on this portion of the shares because it believed that the Chinese stock price would not rebound in the near future .
Ivoru Tzhong &apos;s profit forecast for the fiscal year ending 31 March 2019 is 500 billion yen .
China imposed a 25 % import tariff on US soybeans in July to counter Washington &apos;s trade friction .
Our grain business has been hit by trade frictions between the United States and China , said Yanhiro , the head of the financial department .
He indicated that Gao Hongong had stopped financial transactions in his own account since September .
hong spokesman Pat Burke pointed out in a statement on Friday that the company &apos;s move was in line with internal policy constraints and due to lack of market opportunities .
He also stated that the suspension of financial transactions would not lead to job losses .
Pill Red maintains an annual profit forecast of 230 billion yen , supported by pulp and paper production and power generation .
On Thursday , Sumitomo commercial announced a 16 % increase in profits between April and September , emphasizing that the trade issue between the United States and China has left the future uncertain .
Mitsubishi Commercial Friday raised the annual profit forecast to record levels due to increased coke production and higher prices for commodities such as oil and coal .
Mitsubishi also announced a new business plan to increase its profit for the fiscal year ending 31 March 2022 from the estimated 640 billion yen this year to 900 billion yen ( $ 7.98 billion ) .
