On November 4 , President Donald Trump and his Democratic rivals responded positively to their core constituencies .
Both parties point out that voter turnout will be the key to shaping the election .
Reportedly , 48 hours before the vote in the United States , Trump was busy attending the Republican candidates , while former President Barack Obama went to Indiana to stand for the anxious Democratic Federal Senate candidate Joe Donnelly and shouted the final appeal to the public before the election .
On November 4 , Trump went to Mego , Georgia , to stand for Republican Governor Brian Kempp , saying that on Tuesday you had to go to the polls and you had to vote .
The comparison between the elections is unlikely to be clearer .
Political enthusiasm among voters rose to a rare peak , with some states voting ahead of schedule .
Successive US presidents face the first midterm election , and the number of MPs in his party tends to decline .
According to a new poll published by the Washington Post and ABC News on the 4th , while the Democratic Party &apos;s election campaign for the Federal House of Representatives remains preponderant , Republicans could benefit from economic assessments and Trump &apos;s strong focus on border security .
Polls indicate that registered voters like more Democratic House candidates than Republicans , with a ratio of 50 % to 43 % , but down 14 percentage points from August .
Another poll by the American National Broadcasting Corporation ( NBC ) and the Wall Street Journal also shows that Democrats are still seven percentage points ahead of Republicans .
According to reports , Obama said to the public on the occasion of Senator Donnoli &apos;s rise that when people do not speak the truth , when words no longer represent anything , that will inevitably have negative consequences .
Democracy will not work when people lie only in their own right .
The only way to stop these Republicans &quot; behavior now is by yourself and your vote .
Democrats face the most difficult election in decades in the Senate , with the Republicans now holding more than half of the 51 seats .
But the House election is favorable , and the Democrats need an additional 23 seats to control the 435 @-@ seat House .
Analysts predicting the election website FiveThirtyEight.com estimate that the Democratic Party &apos;s chances of winning the House of Representatives are as high as 85 % .
The CPPCC convened General Secretary Xi Jinping &apos;s Thought Theory Seminar on Strengthening and Improving the Work of the CPPCC , Wang Yang , to attend and address it .
The National People &apos;s Political Consultative Conference held a theoretical seminar on key ideas for General Secretary Xi Jinping on strengthening and improving the work of the People &apos;s Political Consultative Conference in Beijing from 29 to 30 June .
Wang Yang , a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and Chairman of the National People &apos;s Political Consultative Conference , attended the meeting and made a statement .
He stressed that General Secretary Xi Jinping &apos;s important thoughts on strengthening and improving the work of the People &apos;s Political Consultative Conference ( CPPCC ) deeply spelled out the role of the CPPCC , its objectives , its mandate and practical requirements , and that science had answered a series of major questions of a directional , overarching and strategic nature , which were a powerful intellectual weapon guiding the work of the CPPCC in the new era .
We should earnestly learn to implement this important idea , grasp its significance , rich content and spiritual substance , and make practical efforts to understand and understand it , and promote the quality of the work of the CPPCC with theoretical learning and ideological weaponry , and effectively assume the new mission of the CPPCC of the new era .
From 29 to 30 September , the CPPCC convened in Beijing a theoretical seminar on key ideas for strengthening and improving the work of the CPPCC .
Wang Yang pointed out that since the 18th Party Congress , General Secretary Xi Jinping has put forward a series of new ideas and new ideas on strengthening and improving the work of the CPPCC . For the first time , he has put forward the CPPCC as an important channel for socialist consultation and democracy and as a special consultative body . It is an important component of the country &apos;s governance system . It is an institutional arrangement with Chinese characteristics . It is the first time it clarifies the characteristics and strengths of the new party system , emphasizing the relationship between consistency and diversity . It has deeply revealed that the true meaning of the people &apos;s democracy lies in the fact that things are well discussed and people &apos;s affairs are being discussed by the people . It has revealed the logical link between the management of China and the Chinese political system . It has coalesced in the thoughtful thinking of maintaining and developing the CPPCC system . It is the latest result of the party &apos;s theory
Wang Yang stressed that the CPPCC at all levels should take the opportunity of theoretical studies and discussions to further identify weaknesses and shortcomings in the work of the CPPCC , and work hard and seek breakthroughs in strengthening and improving it .
We should fully strengthen the construction of the CPPCC system and ensure that the decision @-@ making and deployment of the Party Central Committee is fully implemented into the work of the CPPCC .
We need to strengthen ideological and political leadership , improve the system , procedures and mechanisms for making proposals for governance and building consensus in both directions , and translate ideological and political leadership into all aspects and processes of carrying out our duties .
We should focus on the performance of duties and responsibilities of the center , better obedience to the Party of Service and the National Bureau , improve the quality of advice and management , and enhance the effectiveness of performing duties .
We should strengthen the construction of the CPPCC itself , take care of the education and training of members and cadres , play the basic role of the Committee of Experts , and strengthen the foundation for the functioning of the CPPCC .
We need to strengthen the direction of the work of the CPPCC and raise the overall level of the work of the CPPCC by setting the direction , setting the example and solving the difficulties .
In order to further study the implementation of the Chinese socialist ideology of the new era of Xi Jinping and the spirit of the 19th National People &apos;s Political Consultative Conference , the system of the National People &apos;s Political Consultative Conference began implementing the important thought @-@ learning and discussion activities of General Secretary Xi Jinping on strengthening and improving the work of the People &apos;s Political Consultative Conference in May , convening eight regional symposiums and seven symposiums of experts and scholars , and identifying 18 key topics and six basic theoretical topics , a total of 793,800 CPC members and 279,000 institutional cadres at all levels participated in the study and discussion sessions , resulting in more than 36,000 research papers .
People &apos;s Net , Beijing , November 5 ( Wang Xiaoyun ) Under the current wave of popular entrepreneurship and mass innovation , a growing number of technology companies have begun to focus on patent research and development and related protection work , deepening the potential value of patents and gaining market dominance .
Likewise , many tech firms have experienced massive abuses in terms of patent technology authorizations , patent technology use , and so on .
At the end of 2017 , Tan Wei , He Zhang Honghong and Lai Bin from Guangdong province applied to the Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court to drop out the developer of APP , Beijing Xiaohu Tech Co . Ltd . ( hereinafter referred to as Xiaohu Tech ) , the operator , and the seller , Guangdong Pacific Internet Information Services Ltd . ( hereinafter referred to as Guangdong Pacific Ocean ) , for patent infringement .
The plaintiff requested the court to order that the defendant immediately cease manufacturing , selling , promising to sell , and using the plaintiff &apos;s patent .
On October 30 , 2018 , the Chinese Judicial Clerk Network published a first instance civil ruling on the dispute over patent rights for inventions with Tan Wei , He Chang @-@ hong , and others , including Beijing Xiaohu Technology Co . , Ltd . , disclosing details of some of the cases in which the drop @-@ out APP had been charged with patent violations .
The three plaintiffs considered that the patent owners and inventors patented by the mobile terminal &apos;s car @-@ sharing service system and method , and that the entire process of operation of the ram car application in the draught @-@ out APP corresponded to the technical solution of the patent protection involved , constituted patent infringement .
However , during the court ruling , Xiaohu Tech believed that the Pacific Ocean in Guangdong was not a suitable defendant , that it only provided free downloads on the Internet of the APP drops involved in the case , that it did not implement the patent method involved , that there was no direct or indirect violation and that it should not be classified as the defendant in the case .
Secondly , the place of violation in the present case is not Guangdong .
Pursuant to the law , the place of infringement of the patent in question should be the place where the patent method in question was implemented in its entirety , and therefore the jurisdiction of the court was challenged and the case was referred to the court in the defendant &apos;s place of residence , the Beijing Intellectual Property Court .
The Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court held that the defendant Guangdong Pacific provided the alleged tort drop @-@ out APP product on its Internet platform and that it was not inappropriate for the plaintiff to list the defendant Guangdong Pacific as the defendant .
And the defendant &apos;s Pacific residence in Guangdong is in Guangzhou City and is under the jurisdiction of the Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court .
The defendant , Xiaohu Tech , claimed that the case should be referred to the Beijing Intellectual Property Court for consideration . On insufficient grounds , the defendant , Xiaohu Tech Ltd. , rejected his challenge to the jurisdiction of the case and assumed the costs of handling the challenge .
Other hearings of the case have not yet been made public , and journalists will follow closely the follow @-@ up details of the case of trickle @-@ down patent abuse .
Interview with the Chief Executive Officer of the Australian Federal Organization for Scientific and Industrial Research ( CSIRO ) : Australian @-@ Chinese cooperation in science and technology has yielded significant results
China &apos;s science and technology have grown rapidly over the past few decades , and Australia and China can achieve fruitful results by working together in science .
Larry Marshall , Chief Executive Officer of the Australian Federal Scientific and Industrial Research Organization , said in an interview with China News Agency reporters in Beijing a few days ago that cooperation between Australia and China in the field of science and technology , from the fight against climate change to the Sino @-@ Pacific Project , is showing momentum .
As Australia &apos;s largest national scientific institution , CSIRO produces many innovative , world @-@ renowned research findings in the oceans , energy , biology , materials , astronomy , and so forth .
CSIRO has maintained close cooperation with scientific institutions such as the Chinese Academy of Sciences .
It is a long @-@ lasting friendship that embodies a tradition of trust in partners and long @-@ standing cooperation , as Marshall put it .
In May of this year , China &apos;s 500 @-@ meter @-@ calibre spherical radio telescope , Indo @-@ China , installed the first international 19 @-@ beam L @-@ band receiver .
This currently state @-@ of @-@ the @-@ art 19 @-@ beam feeder receiver in the world has been jointly developed by Chinese and Australian scientists .
Marshall said that the successful development of the receiver was based on the accumulated technology of CSIRO for many years , and that the FAST cruise speed would increase by a factor of 5 to 6 after commissioning , while at the same time expanding more scientific observation targets .
This is the strength of CSIRO &apos;s contribution to FAST .
In addition to this cooperation , CSIRO works closely with Chinese research institutions on the construction of square kilometre array radio telescopes , the development of new fuel technologies , and energy conservation and emission reduction .
Previous scientific research has tended to focus on the problems of hundreds of years later , and more research is needed now to address the problems at hand .
Marshall argues that Australia and China are complementary in the field of scientific development , and that both countries face a range of challenges in their development .
For example , extreme weather events are frequent globally , drought and floods have led to reduced food production , and food shortages have severely affected human development .
At the same time , the problems of population explosion , ageing and chronic diseases are serious challenges .
The cooperation between Australia and China in recent years has focused primarily on solving these immediate problems .
Marshall said that the International Centre for the Study of the Southern Hemisphere Ocean , established by CSIRO in cooperation with the National Laboratory for Marine Science and Technology in Qingdao , focused on observing the El Niño and La Niña phenomena , studying their relationship to extreme weather and establishing early warning facilities for extreme weather ; new cereal varieties developed by CSIRO in cooperation with the Chinese Academy of Sciences to overcome extreme weather could also alleviate the food shortage caused by extreme weather .
Given the current environment , where science , technology and innovation are difficult to accomplish on their own , require extremely high costs , and there are many problems to be solved , cooperation is particularly important today .
Marshall said that the closer the cooperation , the more likely it will be to make breakthrough progress , which is also the meaning of enhanced cooperation between Australia and China under the framework of the &quot; one belt , one road . &quot;
Increased bilateral cooperation is , for us , mainly in the field of science and technology .
Marshall , for example , recently developed a cyanide @-@ free gold purification method in CSIRO , in which many countries want to find a way to purify gold that is less polluting .
We are very willing to introduce this technology into China , which is one of the results of our cooperation in the region .
