The offices of the Urumqi City Merchants Bureau , the Commerce Bureau , the Agricultural and Pastoral Affairs Bureau , the Tourism Bureau and some 500 people from enterprises and the media participated in the plea .
Northeast revitalization is about the overall state of national development .
Northeast industrial enterprises are bigger and better @-@ based . For Northeast Asia , catching innovation means catching development , and seeking innovation means seeking the future .
Can the vitality of the old industrial base be rekindled and released to the heart of the General Secretary ?
North Korean Foreign Minister Lee Yung Hao told the United Nations on Saturday that the continued imposition of sanctions is deepening North Korea &apos;s mistrust of the United States , and North Korea cannot unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons under such circumstances .
At the United Nations General Assembly , Lee Yong Hao said that North Korea had taken a very friendly approach over the past year , including halting its missile and nuclear tests , dismantling its nuclear test sites and committing itself to the non @-@ proliferation of nuclear weapons and technology .
However , we did not see any corresponding response from the United States , which he said .
If we do not trust the United States , we will not have confidence in our national security , and under such circumstances we cannot give up our weapons unilaterally .
Although Lee Yong Hao repeats North Korea &apos;s complaint that the US is opposed to a phased denuclearization , his speech is significant , because he did not reject unilateral denuclearization at all , as North Korea did before .
Lee Yong @-@ hao referred to the June 12 joint statement between Kim Jong @-@ un and Trump , when Kim agreed to move toward denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula , and Trump promised to protect North Korea &apos;s security .
North Korea has been seeking to officially end the 1950 @ -53 Korean War , but the US says that North Korea must give up its nuclear weapons first .
The US has also refused to relax its demands for international sanctions against North Korea .
The United States insisted on first denuclearizing it ; and increased the pressure on sanctions to achieve their objectives under high pressure , and even refused to issue a declaration on the end of the war ; Li Yonghao called it .
The idea that sanctions will allow us to kneel and seek relief is that we do not know that our people are dreaming of the day .
The problem , however , is that such continued sanctions are deepening our mistrust .
Li Yonghao did not mention the second special gold conference program that the US president mentioned earlier this week at the United Nations .
Instead , he highlighted three meetings between Kim Jong @-@ un and South Korean President Moon Moon over the past five months , saying that denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula would not become so deadlocked if the other side of denuclearization was South Korea , not North Korea .
China announced a reduction in import tariffs for 1,585 tax items , effective 1 November 2018 .
Since this year , China has taken a series of initiatives to reduce import tariffs .
An across @-@ the @-@ board tax cut on medicines on May 1 this year adjusted import tariffs to zero for a total of 28 tax items , including anti @-@ cancer drugs and anticancer @-@ resistant alkaloids , Chinese medicines with actual imports , etc .
At the same time , the value @-@ added tax on anti @-@ cancer drug production and import links has been reduced considerably .
Tax reductions were made on vehicles and spare parts for 218 tax purposes on 1 July .
After the tax cuts , the entire car rate in China has been lower than the average in developing countries , in line with the reality of the Chinese automotive industry .
This tax cut will promote industrial restructuring and the optimal allocation of resources , accelerate the improvement of quality and sustenance , help improve the quality of products and services , and hopefully drive some adjustment in automobile prices to make them more affordable to consumers .
Tax reductions on consumer goods were made on 1 July for 1,449 tax items .
Cuts in taxes on consumer goods are inextricably linked to people &apos;s needs for a better life .
This time , tax cuts were not only numerous but also substantial , averaging 56 per cent .
Cuts in taxes on consumer goods were used to benefit consumers directly and to promote competitiveness in domestic industries .
A tax reduction will be implemented on industrial goods such as electromechanical equipment , spare parts and raw materials for 1,585 tax items on 1 November .
An appropriate reduction in import tariffs for some of the country &apos;s much @-@ needed industrial goods could attract more foreign investment , help to increase effective domestic supply and boost industrial upgrading , while helping enterprises allocate resources globally , reduce production costs and reduce pressures on domestic environmental carrying .
The relevant head of the Office of the State Council &apos;s Customs and Excise Commission said that the above @-@ mentioned four autonomous tax reductions , as well as the third @-@ step tax cuts implemented on 1 July of this year as a result of the negotiations on the expansion of the scope of the information technology agreement , would reduce China &apos;s total tariff level from 9.8 per cent in the previous year to 7.5 per cent .
The total level of adjusted tariffs is slightly higher than in the European Union , below most developing countries , and is moderately low , broadly matching China &apos;s developing country status and stage of development .
The person in charge said that the overall level of tariffs , as one of the important indicators of China &apos;s openness in the area of trade in goods , should correspond to the stage of China &apos;s economic development and reflect the characteristics of the times .
China &apos;s trade in goods was the largest in the world and already had an economic base for further expansion of openness , but the quality and effectiveness of trade development differed from that of developed economies , and the overall level of tariffs should therefore be reduced appropriately .
Tariffs are a means of protection against compliance , the level of which should be commensurate with industrial competitiveness , encourage benign competition , and overprotect against industrial development and improve quality .
Tariff rate adjustments need to balance production and consumption needs .
Focusing on lowering the commodity tax rate , which is high in domestic demand and contributes to the upgrading of industrial transformation , efforts have been made to increase the import of niche products where the demand of the masses is more concentrated , and to continuously increase the sense of access of enterprises and the public to meet the upgrading needs of industrial and consumer structures .
Tax reductions need to balance fiscal revenues with the affordability of industrial development .
There is a need to harmonize the relationship between domestic and foreign markets , upstream and downstream , and between production and consumption in the choice of specific tax @-@ cutting goods and the extent of tax reductions , in order to maintain the positive trend in China &apos;s economic stability .
The person in charge stressed that this year marks the fortieth anniversary of reform and opening @-@ up , and that China &apos;s initiative to reduce the overall level of import tariffs is a major initiative in line with China &apos;s own need to achieve high @-@ quality development , and is conducive to the integrated use of both international and foreign resources , promoting the quality improvement of the domestic supply system and meeting the needs of the public for consumer upgrading .
Such actions and initiatives demonstrate China &apos;s unwavering commitment to a mutually beneficial opening @-@ up strategy , its firm support for economic globalization , its firm commitment to the principles of free trade and a multilateral trading system with WTO at its core , and its continued development momentum from opening up to the world and making China &apos;s development more beneficial to the world .
Serbia announced that it will enter the highest operational readiness . President Serbian and Russian will meet tomorrow to discuss the situation in Kosovo .
ccording to information from the Office of the President of Serbia , the President of Serbia , Vučić , ordered the armed forces of Kosovo to reach the highest operational readiness in view of the occupation by the Kosovo Special Forces of access to the water storage lake at the Ghazvoda hydroelectric station in northern Kosovo , which is controlled by the Belgrade side .
On 29 September , Serbian Defence Minister Vulin declared that the Serbian army was in full operational readiness .
Vulin stressed that Serbia would continue to monitor the current situation in Kosovo as long as the orders issued by Vučić remained in force and that the Serb army would respond regardless of the direction of events .
According to a Russian Tas News Agency report , on September 29 , Vučić said in an interview that he had briefed the United States , Russia , and Europe on the current situation and would go to Moscow on October 2 to meet Russian President Putin and seek Putin &apos;s support on the Kosovo issue .
When asked whether Serbia needs Russia &apos;s military support , as in Syria , Vučić replied in the negative : I do not want a major military conflict on our territory .
Vučić also stated that the full operational readiness of the Serb Army was intended only to serve as a deterrent to prevent the outbreak of the conflict , but it was also a clear warning that any violence in Kosovo would never be tolerated .
The increased operational readiness of the Serb Army is linked to two major moves on the Kosovo side .
According to the Serbian side , in recent days Albanians have been arresting Serbs who have lived in northern Kosovo for generations without violating any law .
Vučić said that since the beating and detention of Marco Juric , head of the Serbian Government &apos;s office in Kosovo and Metohija , by the Kosovo Albanian Army on 26 March this year , the Albanian community has escalated the situation in the region and unhumanely arrested and expelled Serbs .
In addition , more than 100 people , including the recently self @-@ proclaimed ROSU Special Forces of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Republic of Kosovo , armed police and snipers , occupied positions near the water lake at the Ghazvoda hydroelectric power station , entered ecological and sports centres near dams in the northern part of the Kosovo region and blocked all nearby roads , which were otherwise controlled by the Serbian side .
Vučić points out that this military adventure by Kosovo was instigated by Western countries and that the Kosovo Army did not notify the Serbian side beforehand , in violation of Chapter 9 , paragraph 1 , of the Brussels Agreement , as well as United Nations Security Council Resolution 1244 and the military @-@ technical agreement between Seko .
Vučić has already spoken to NATO Secretary @-@ General Stoltenberg criticizing the hypocritical rhetoric of Western countries on Kosovo .
The root cause of the current conflict remains centuries of historical animosity between the Serb and Albanian communities in the Kosovo region .
There are separate accounts of Kosovo &apos;s affiliation between Serbs and Albanians .
Serbia views Kosovo as the birthplace and cultural cradle of its people , as Serbia built its own most powerful state here in the twelfth century , and Albanians moved in large numbers only after the Ottoman invasion and the fall of the Serb army .
The Albanians , for their part , insist that the original tribe of 4 @ -@ 5 B.C. , the Illians , who lived in Kosovo in the fifth century , is an ethnic Albanian ancestor and , therefore , Kosovo has been an ethnic Albanian territory since ancient times .
Subjective political divisions have led to intense ethnic , religious and cultural strife and violent confrontation between Serbs and Albanians in the Kosovo region .
In 1912 , the Kosovo Albanians first declared the independence of Albania .
After the First World War , a large number of ethnic Albanians living in the Balkans moved to Turkey , with a relative increase in the proportion of Serbs , who , in the eyes of the Serbs , simply took back their land , but were perceived by the Albanians as a plunder of Serbian chauvinism , exacerbating the conflict between the two communities .
Kosovo has become a barrels of fire in the Balkans .
In 1999 , armed clashes between Albanian separatists of the Kosovo Liberation Army ( KLA ) and the Serbian army and police led to the bombing by NATO forces of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia , composed of Serbia and Montenegro , and the outbreak of the war in Kosovo .
On 17 February 2008 , Kosovo unilaterally declared its independence from Serbia .
Since then , despite news that Serbia would normalize its relations with Kosovo and sign a global and legally binding agreement , it has not been able to do so , owing to historical national grievances and geopolitical constraints .
A month ago , for the first time , Vučić made clear his preference for the separation of Serbs from Albanians in Kosovo and for the reopening of the conflict between the two communities .
Electricity communications were still interrupted , and Indonesia &apos;s strong earthquake was accompanied by tsunami relief difficulties
According to figures released by the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency in the early morning hours of the 30th , a strong earthquake and tsunami in Donggara district in Central Sulawesi province of the country occurred on the 28th , killing 420 people .
The head of the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency , WilemRampangilei , said that the figure was only a preliminary estimate for the city of Palu , the capital of Central Sulawesi province , some 80 kilometres from the epicentre of the earthquake , because many of the city &apos;s densely populated buildings , such as hotels , shops and warehouses , damaged by the collapse of the earthquake had not been searched and rescued because of the lack of large search and rescue machinery .
On 29 September 2018 , local time , Pakistan Road , Indonesia , broke down a bridge damaged by the earthquake and tsunami .
As a result of the severe damage to electricity and communications , the Central Donggara district and the neighbouring Siji area remain inaccessible islands to date , making it impossible to count the number of victims .
ccording to media reports this time , Vice President Kara of Indonesia said that thousands or thousands of people had died .
Power outages , disruption of communications , road blockages , damage to airports and post @-@ tsunami relief efforts were difficult .
Owing to power outages , some hospitals and relief settlements in the city of Palu depend on fuel for electricity generation .
Access to the city was blocked by landslides that prevented large transport vehicles , including oil tankers , from reaching the city , straining fuel supplies .
Indonesian Minister of Social Affairs Agus said that emergency relief items such as tents , mattresses , blankets , clothing , food and household kits transferred by the Ministry from South Sulawesi and Gorontalo provinces adjacent to the earthquake zone had not yet arrived in the affected areas due to road damage .
Disaster relief consignments from the capital Jakarta are being transported to the affected areas by air transport aircraft .
In view of the damage to the Pallu airport command tower and runway during the earthquake , all commercial flights have been halted for the sole purpose of securing and securing relief supplies and for the landing and landing of military aircraft transporting relief supplies and personnel .
Indonesian Minister for Political , Legal and Security Affairs , Wiranto , who commanded the rescue in the earthquake zone , called for the early restoration of electricity supply and airfield commercial flight services to ensure the functioning of relief agencies such as hospitals and allow more relief workers and volunteers and aid supplies to reach the affected areas .
On the 28th , there were repeated strong earthquakes in Donggara district , Middle Sulawesi province , Indonesia . These included a 7.7 magnitude strong earthquake at 1702 hours local time , which triggered a tsunami , resulting in major disaster events in the cities of Palu , Donggara and Siji .
Xinhua News Agency , Beijing , October 1 ( Reporter Yin Li ) - In recent days , Bishui , Qinghuan , Qinghuan , Qinghuan , and Qinghuan , Beijing has continued to open the most beautiful blue @-@ skies model , drawing hundreds of thousands of people from the city of Beijing to a flower image on a social platform , and feeling comfortable on a continuous screen , calling it a cramped blue white cloud , drunk over apos ; America &apos;s sky line , this is the best famous piece in Beijing .
Since August , Beijing has welcomed the most blue sky .
Within the city of Beijing , people can be seen anywhere in the city either holding smartphones or holding single @-@ camera photos .
On social platforms such as Weibo , WeChat and the circle of friends , the Imperial Palace , Tiananmen &apos;s Gate , Bird &apos;s Nest , and Hu Di &apos;idi buildings in the screen of netizens display different beauties under the blue lining .
Some netizens said that such a large swathes of the storm were the best city propaganda film in Beijing ; others quipped that if such blue skies were to be screened for a long time , people with cervical vertebrates would be cured ; and some netizens hoped that the blue skins would be wiped out in winter and spring summer , allowing the Beijing City &apos;s natural curtain to be cloudy in the fourth quarter .
Why do the people in Beijing particularly love the sun of the blue sky ?
Just because the people who lived in this city in the past suffered from haze , they were particularly yearning for the blue sky , and after Beijing launched a battle to defend the blue sky , the air quality continued to improve , the haze decreased , the blue sky increased , and the people looked at their hearts with happiness , and the happiness gained was particularly weighty .
On the day of the National Day , the weather in Beijing was fine .
At 8 a.m. , the vast majority of the 35 air quality monitoring stations throughout the city were shown to be first @-@ class beautiful green .
A popular and spontaneous photographic competition on social platforms on the topic of the blue skies is continuing .
Why has the sky in Beijing been so blue lately ?
According to the relevant person in charge of the Beijing Municipal Environmental Protection Agency , in August this year , the average concentration of fine particulate matter ( PM2.5 ) in Beijing was 35 μg / m3 , which is the best record in the past five years .
In September , PM2.5 concentrations in real time were even more frequent in single digits .
A major factor contributing to the emergence of the blue sky is the overall favourable weather conditions in recent times , and more importantly , Beijing &apos;s persistent efforts to combat air pollution , its vigorous promotion of a clean air action plan over the past five years , and its sustained release of environmental benefits , which have resulted in a reduction in total pollutant emissions in the region , all of which have laid the foundation for sustained improvement in air quality .
Beijing officially launched and implemented the Beijing City 2013 @ - @ 2017 Clean Air Action Plan in 2013 .
Under the plan , official guidance continued to be directed to the non @-@ capital functions to advance energy cleaning alternatives and pollution abatement efforts , phasing out a total of 4923 coal @-@ fired boilers .
As a result , Beijing became the first large city in mainland China to be gas @-@ free .
The data show that between 2013 and 2017 , the cumulative annual concentration of PM2.5 in Beijing decreased by 35.6 per cent ; air quality compliance increased by 50 days ; class I excellence increased by 25 days ; heavy contamination decreased by a total of 35 days ; and the incidence of heavy contamination decreased significantly .
While air quality continues to improve , Beijing government released the Beijing Municipal Three @-@ Year Plan of Action for Winning the Blue Sky Defense Battle in September of this year , based on a new round of PM2.5 source analysis , focusing on key prevention and control areas such as diesel trucks , dust , volatile organic matter management , optimizing transport structure , industrial structure , energy structure , and land use structure , strengthening regional joint defense and control , focusing on improving urban fine @-@ tuning management , comprehensively promoting green development , and striving to get the Blue Square to stay in the city of Beijing , so that it can no longer use scarcity as a precious source and return it to the background rather than the main role of people .
During this year &apos;s National Day Golden Week , the relevant departments of the City Tourism Commission , business and industry , city management , and public security will strengthen law enforcement inspection of the one @-@ day visit to the market , focusing on the six black spots in the tourism industry , and once the violators are found guilty , they will be severely and severely punished in accordance with the law .
Yesterday morning , the city government convened a special meeting on the topic of crackdowns on illegal daily trips to deploy special actions to further crack down on illegal daily trips .
At the meeting , it was revealed that focusing on the black ticket , the black guide , the black market , the black car , the black store , and the mixed chain of interests of the black network , the city had launched a special campaign to crack down on the illegal one @-@ day trip since July 28 .
To date , 39 complaints of daily visits have been received , a decrease of 63 per cent over the previous year . Since this year , 270 complaints of daily trips have been received , a decrease of 62 per cent .
In the past two months , the city has seized 248 black cars , investigated and punished 158 violations of tourist passenger traffic regulations , closed 29 shopping houses and entertainers , investigated and punished 13 black houses and 27 black guides , confiscated 26,000 illegal advertisements , dismantled 31 illegal day @-@ trip billboards and 3 false billboards , investigated and punished 1,789 violations of various types of travel offences , registered 181 cases by various functional departments , severely fined 4.48 million yuan , and detained 111 persons involved in the travel .
After correction , the chaos of the illegal one @-@ day trip was basically contained , and the order of the one @-@ day trip to the market showed a steady and positive trend .
It is said that in recent years , the city has continuously increased its efforts to rectify the illegal one @-@ day travels .
In 2016 and 2017 , the City Tourist Committee received 1612 and 897 complaints of daily trips , a decrease of 79 per cent and 44 per cent , respectively , compared to the previous year , but the illegal daily trips continued to be repeated and rebounded , creating a mixed picture of the chain of interests of black ticketing , black guide , black market , black car , black shop and black network .
Specifically , illegal street guests , namely , the black ticket , the illegal website that publishes false tourism information , the black net , the travel agency or institution or individual that engages in illegal day @-@ to @-@ day trips or does not have the qualifications to operate the travel agency , the black market , the guided tour employed by the black market , which is not licensed or practiced illegally , the black market , the vehicle that uses the unqualified tourist passenger transport , or the tourist passenger @-@ qualified vehicle that provides passenger services for the illegal day trip , which is the &quot; black car crash , &quot; and ultimately the designated tourist shopping shop that they bring tourists into , which is the black store .
In this special operation , the city continuously increased its fixed inspection and motorized inspection of illegal daily visits . In response to the high incidence and high impact of illegal daily visits , the relevant departments dispatched secret inspection teams to carry out unannounced visits every day , and after finding evidence of violations , they strictly investigated and punished in accordance with the law .
Among them , the crash and the crash shop became the focus of two of the special operations .
According to the introduction , without a black car , it will not be possible to travel on a day @-@ to @-@ day basis . The black car can be easily discovered , remembered and investigated , and is also a single fixed asset of higher value .
Relevant departments have used road traffic surveillance probes to increase the supervision of high @-@ priority pilgrimage buses , using technical and physical intelligence to find and deal with them in a timely manner .
Due to the small number of tourist shopping malls and the fact that they operate on the ground , the focus has also become heavy .
In order to strengthen the deterrence and crackdown on illegal day @-@ to @-@ day travel , all departments in special operations that find violations of the law have been given heavier and heavier punishments in accordance with the law .
In August of this year , the city also held a seminar on legal issues related to the severe suppression of illegal labour , and discussed measures to combine administrative punishment with criminalization .
The City Tourist Committee said that in the future , more regular travel agencies will be encouraged to carry out the Beijing Days and Days and increase the supply of regular Days and Days to further squeeze the living space of the illegal Days and Days . Specific programmes are still under study .
In addition , the City Tourist Committee is continuously refining the Tourist Mission e @-@ itinerary information system to ensure that each team is included in the eitinerary platform supervision .
From a tourist symbol to a digital economic symbol , what did the town experience these years ?
As the permanent venue of the World Internet Congress , attention has been paid to how the town can take over the summit dividend .
Since the first World Internet Congress , changes in the town of Uu have been evident in the past five years .
In 2014 , there were only 12 businesses in the town related to the digital economy and the Internet , and by the third quarter of this year there were more than 500 .
This is a microcosm of the development of the digital economy in the town of Uu .
The Internet conference allowed local firms to accept the digital economy at zero distance and the inspiration of the digital wave . There was a strong desire for business transformation , and traditional manufacturing firms increased their investment and research and development in machine exchange , smart management , and so on .
Kang Wei , Secretary of the Party Committee of Wucheng Township , said that Wucheng Township will build a new economic empowerment center in the future .
The development of the digital economy cannot be sustained without infrastructure .
This year , the town launched the 5G pilot project on the basis of full coverage of the 4G communications network and free WiFi .
At the same time , the city of Taoqiang , where the town of Uu is located , has also become a hot ground for the development of the Internet industry as the first county @-@ level city in the country to build a dedicated international Internet data channel .
Since the first World Internet Congress , a total of 565 projects in the digital economy category have been introduced , with a total planned investment of 37.725 billion yuan . In the first three quarters of this year , a total of 8.73 billion yuan has been set aside for core manufacturing in the digital economy , representing an increase in value added of 13 per cent year on year .
