Active treatment , China has achieved a survival rate of 98 per cent for premature births of 29 weeks or more , reaching the level of developed countries .
Chinanews.com , Shanghai , September 30 ( Chen Jing , Luo Yanqian ) - The National Children &apos;s Medical Center and Fudan University &apos;s affiliated paediatric hospital revealed on the 30th that they have introduced advanced Canadian methods in the leading NICU project to improve the quality of pre @-@ natal care in China .
The project results show that , after active treatment , China has achieved a survival rate of 98 per cent for children born prematurely in 29 weeks or more , reaching the level of developed countries , but that there is still considerable room for improvement in the survival rate of very young children born prematurely and without complications .
For almost two decades , the Chinese government has been paying attention to the treatment of newborns .
At present , infant mortality in the Shanghai region has fallen to 3.71 per cent , significantly below the national average and to advanced levels in developed countries .
China &apos;s NICU project to improve the quality of life of premature babies in hospital has greatly improved the quality of life of premature babies through four years of unremitting efforts .
Professor Cao Yun , Director of the Neonatal Intensive Care Unit ( NICU ) at Fudan University &apos;s affiliated paediatric hospital , told the reporter that while raising the survival rate of premature babies , paying attention to reducing the quality of survival of premature babies , reducing the incidence of complications , improving neurodevelopmental forecasting , and improving the overall outcome of affected children is important for improving the overall quality of life and demographic quality of premature babies . It is an important concern of the national and foreign paediatric and neonatal communities . It is also a key concern of this project .
China &apos;s NICU project to improve the quality of prenatal care for premature children in hospital through four years of unremitting efforts has brought together tens of thousands of premature births aged 33 weeks and under across the country , resulting in a one @-@ third reduction in infant mortality and low birth weight premature births in the country , as well as a significant reduction in the incidence of serious complications among premature children , which has greatly improved the quality of life of premature children .
Through the establishment of a nationwide network for improving the quality of newborns and the introduction of collaborative quality improvement concepts , the project has irradiated 25 collaborative hospitals across China , creating a collaborative quality improvement method for improving the early delivery of babies and improving the quality of care for newborns that is appropriate to national conditions .
The Paediatric Hospital attached to Fudan University is working with the national neonatal department to develop guidelines for the treatment and treatment of neonatal infections , based on the accumulated experience of the project , and to provide reference and guidance for the standardized treatment and treatment of neonatal infections in China .
According to reports , in the China Early Childbirth Prospective Quality Improvement Project , paediatric hospitals introduced the EPIQ method into 25 large NICUs in 19 provinces of the country , working to address the problem of premature birth infections that plague China &apos;s neonatal care units .
After more than a decade of continuous improvement , Canada &apos;s national survival rate for premature births has increased by about a third , and it is now one of the best in the world .
The EPIQ approach has now been applied to all NICUs across Canada and has been adopted for application in six countries .
For its part , paediatric hospitals revealed that two years after the EPIQ intervention , premature birth infections decreased by 35 per cent , while antibiotic use decreased by 20 per cent .
In the future , Fudan University &apos;s Paediatric Hospital will continue to promote and implement this approach nationwide , with a view to comprehensively reducing the incidence of all complications among premature babies and improving the quality of care for newborns throughout the country .
At the present time , it is indisputable that the level of treatment in various regions of China varies and is uneven .
According to Professor Cao Yun , as an important construction unit of the National Children &apos;s Medical Centre , paediatric hospitals will play a leading role in radiation . This study covers several western provinces such as Xinjiang , Guizhou , Gansu and Shaanxi , with a view to gradually promoting homogenization and regularization of neonatal treatment nationwide .
According to reports , Fudan University &apos;s affiliated paediatric hospital is working with the national neonatal department to develop guidelines for the treatment and treatment of neonatal infections , based on the accumulated experience of the project , and to provide reference and guidance for the standard treatment and treatment of neonatal infections in China .
It was revealed that in 2019 , the China Neonatal Collaborative Network , located at Fudan University &apos;s affiliated paediatric hospital , would work with 63 hospitals across the country to carry out the next stage of quality improvement nationwide , with a view to promoting the homogenization of treatment levels for newborns in China .
uo Shuli , director of the Shanghai Municipal Health and Family Planning Commission , said that Shanghai can become a central city in Asia , not only in research , but also in the construction of the entire service system , the quality of service and the results of service should all have a place in Asia , thus truly reflecting China &apos;s medical standard .
Sincere : The memorial to the heroes in my heart was written on the occasion of the fifth Martyrs &apos; Day .
On September 30 , on the eve of the Republic &apos;s 69 @-@ year @-@ old Christmas , we celebrated the fifth Martyrs Day , when Xi Jinping and other party and state leaders came to Tiananmen Square to attend a wreath @-@ laying ceremony for the people &apos;s heroes .
At this juncture , no matter where you may be , please pay a fervent tribute .
The Day of Remembrance is a comeback , and even more awakening .
Turning back on a heavy history , the name of each martyr is a living life .
They also have a hot youth , a sincere love , and a hungry family .
However , because they firmly believe in our faith @-@ based ideology , it is the truth of the universe that they are willing to sacrifice everything of their own in order to save the suffering of the next generation .
One day I survive , I will call for one day for China .
Through time and space , the heroes set up a mental road sign to guide the way forward .
Where do you come from , where do you go and do what kind of people do ? It is not difficult to get an answer .
Commemoration of the heroes and , above all , the erection of a monument to the heroes in their hearts .
According to incomplete statistics , some 20 million martyrs have sacrificed their lives for national independence , people &apos;s liberation , and the country &apos;s rich and powerful since the days of the Revolutionary War .
Many martyrs did not even leave their names behind for various reasons .
Countless heroes breed their ideals with blood , practicing their faith with life , remembering their honour and passing on their spirit is to protect the roots and souls of the nation .
The memorial to the heroes must not be tainted or vandalized .
For some time now , the dark currents of historical nihilism , pan @-@ entertainment , and so on have proliferated .
All sorts of distorted history and derogatory practices challenge the conscience of justice , distort value judgments , and arouse public outrage and alarm throughout society .
The heroes must not be blasphemy , and the heroes must not forget .
The act of touching the bottom line cannot be allowed to go unpunished and must dare to show its sword and defend the heroic dignity with justice and the rule of law .
On 1 May this year , the Law on the Protection of Heroes &apos; Martyrs was officially implemented .
Judging from judicial practice , the judgments in some cases were extremely popular , effectively safeguarding the brilliant image in accordance with the law , while unleashing the positive energy of celebrating heroes and admiring martyrdom .
A aspiring people cannot be without heroes , and an ideal country cannot be without pioneers .
Paying tribute to the memory of the martyrs and calling upon the heroes has become a universal social consensus .
At present , there are a total of millions of commemorative facilities in the country , with more than 100 million visits to martyr gardens each year .
People &apos;s hearts are the strongest building blocks .
Let the glorification of heroes , the defence of heroes , the study of heroes and the care of heroes become the norm , and integrate the spirit of heroism into the blood of the nation . A memorial to the heroes will stand firmly between the earth and deep in the hearts and minds .
BRUSSELS , September 28 - The European Union took a non @-@ confrontational stance on Italy on Friday , after Italy flouted EU demands and surprised markets with large budget deficits , but the EU may take a more radical stance if Italy insists on too bold a goal .
Italy &apos;s Euroskeptic government aims to run a budget deficit equivalent to 2.4 % of gross domestic product ( GDP ) over the next three years , suggesting that there has been no debt reduction in the face of a deficit demand .
European Commission Executive Committee Executive Committee on Economic Affairs member Moscosi said on Friday that we had no interest in the crisis between the Commission and Italy , and he responded cautiously , given that EU proposals and sanctions could have little impact on Italy .
EU officials and diplomats remain hopeful that market forces will persuade Italy to adjust its budget plan before Italy formally submits it to the Commission in mid @-@ October .
After the government announced its plan , the euro fell to its lowest level in nearly two weeks on Friday , and Italian bond yields reached their highest level in three weeks .
If the deficit target remains unchanged until the October deadline , the Commission could veto Italy &apos;s proposed budget , as it has never done for any country .
At a subsequent meeting in Riga , the Latvian capital , on Friday , the EU Commission Vice President Doblovsky said that Italy &apos;s current fiscal plan seemed to be inconsistent with the Stability and Growth Pact , referring to the EU &apos;s fiscal rules .
But he did not say how this would trigger an EU response .
