Nearly 1,000 state @-@ owned attractions reduced their ticket prices by more than 20 %
# 91 ; Summary # 93 . As of September 28 , 981 scenic areas had been opened or reduced free of charge ( 74 opened free of charge and 907 reduced ) , rock forests in Yunnan , Dali Three Towers , Yulongxuan Mountains , Guilin Lijiang in Guangxi , Wurai Mountain in Fujian , Zhang Jiabi in Hunan , Shaanxi Ha &apos;aoo in Shaanxi , Sanqing Mountain in Jiangxi , and Kanas in Xinjiang have all implemented price reductions .
In order to follow up on the implementation of the decision @-@ making and deployment of the Central Economic Work Conference and the Government Work Report , the National Development Reform Commission issued on June 28 &quot; Guidance on perfecting the mechanism for forming ticket prices in state @-@ owned attractions to reduce ticket prices in key state @-@ owned attractions &quot; ( hereinafter referred to as the Guidance ) , which calls for perfecting the mechanism for forming ticket prices in state @-@ owned attractions in terms of rationalizing the composition of ticket pricing costs , innovative price management methods , strict enforcement of pricing procedures , etc . , and ensuring tangible results in reducing the prices of ticket prices in high @-@ priority state @-@ owned attractions by September .
In accordance with deployment requirements , localities have actively worked to reduce the prices of tickets in a number of key state @-@ owned attractions .
As of September 28 , 981 scenes had been opened or reduced free of charge ( 74 were opened free of charge and 907 reduced ) , 159 of them in the 5A category and 534 in the 4A level , for a total of 693 ( 70.6 % ) .
Of the 907 attractions , 491 decreased by more than 20 per cent , or 54.3 per cent , and 214 decreased by more than 30 per cent , or 23.6 per cent .
The provinces of Yunnan , Shandong , Guangxi and Shaanxi have a higher number of price reduction attractions , including Yunnan , where the number of price reduction attractions exceeds 100 , with an overall decrease of more than 30 per cent .
All eight provinces ( districts and cities ) including Anhui and Chongqing have achieved price reductions for 5A @-@ grade scenes .
Price reductions have been implemented in such scenic areas as Yunnan Shilin , Dali Three Towers , Yulong Xishan , Guangxi Guilin , Fujian Wurai Hills , Hunan Zhang Family , Shaanxi Wuyu , Jiangxi Sanqing Hills , Xinjiang Kanas , etc .
The gradual return of ticket prices to reasonable ranges in key state @-@ owned attractions is conducive to accelerating the transition of tourism from the ticket economy to the industrial economy , small @-@ scale tourism to mass tourism , and attraction tourism to region @-@ wide tourism . It is also beneficial to create a virtuous circle of optimizing the supply structure of tourism and steadily expanding the demand for tourism and consumption , and to promoting the sustainable and healthy development of attraction areas and tourism .
At the same time , the National Development and Reform Commission stressed the need for all places to strengthen the norms of price order in scenic areas , guide scenic areas to upgrade services , and ensure that prices do not fall .
In addition , the National Development Reform Commission has carried out special supervision on such issues as the small decrease in ticket prices in individual scenic areas and the non @-@ decline in real terms , as reflected by the media recently , and has asked all regions to seriously address them , respond to social concerns in a timely manner , and effectively implement the reduction in prices .
Trade and Development Board to carry out an orderly process of medium- and long @-@ term optimization
The Macao Trade and Investment Promotion Authority has submitted short- and long @-@ term optimization reports on major investment migrants and skilled migrants . In addition to stepping up the promotion and implementation of the activities contained in the reports , the Macao Trade and Investment Promotion Authority has been continuously consulting with society and continuously optimizing the content of the reports and related work .
The TPB will introduce relevant optimization to all sectors of society as soon as possible .
Five of these were short @-@ term measures undertaken during the year ; five were medium @-@ term measures undertaken in 2019 ; and one was long @-@ term measures .
In addition , the TPB conducted a comprehensive review of the internal management system , as directed by the Director of the Department of Economics and Finance , Liang Wit .
The five short @-@ term measures undertaken during the year include :
1 . Carry out a review process . Give priority to those cases that are about to expire for seven years , those referred to in the ICAC report , and new renewal cases . If cases are found to contain signs of misconduct or violations , they will be referred to the relevant judicial authorities for follow @-@ up ;
2 . Field visits to projects involving major investments in migrants . More than 20 investment projects were visited by late September ;
3 . A comprehensive review of the current evaluation system . Six principles have been re @-@ established for the analysis of investment projects with regard to the evaluation of &quot; major investment immigrants &quot; applications . In the evaluation of &quot; technology immigrants &quot; applications , the relevant approval mechanism will be improved through the identification of elements that have a positive impact on the development of the Macao SAR and the conditions for the preferential absorption of talent .
4 . Continuous efforts to increase transparency of information , including plans to gradually publish approval guidelines , rating criteria and percentages , and to further refine and make publicly available data on approval starting from the fourth quarter of this year ;
5 . In terms of improving the work of the recognition mechanism , pre @-@ recognition checks have been required for work in Australia ; significant investments have to be verified on site and financial statements submitted .
The five medium @-@ term measures undertaken in 2019 include :
1 . Establishment of a mechanism for regular hearings with the Commission on Human Development and the Commission on Economic Development , in which a working meeting was held with the Commission on Economic Development in September to discuss the establishment of such a mechanism .
2 . Require applicants to submit annually financial statements made by independent third parties to keep the operation of investment projects under review ;
3 . Further standardize and electronically the process of case requests and approvals in order to reduce human error ;
4 . A comprehensive review of current staffing levels , in conjunction with the implementation of a number of optimization measures ;
5 . Expedite work on the revision of the Temporary Residence Regime for Investors , Managers and Specially Qualified Technicians .
As far as the long @-@ term measures are concerned , research into the law has been intensified , and work is expected in the first half of 2019 on drafting the relevant legislation with a view to completing it as soon as possible , further clarifying the criteria for granting temporary residence permits , the review mechanism and the confirmation mechanism , and increasing the investigative function of the Trade and Development Board in order to more precisely approve and regulate applications for temporary residence permits .
Experts from the national film @-@ free cotton field watching and discussion exchange activities entered the test field and heard a briefing by a representative of the Yu Shunxun team of the Chinese Academy of Engineering .
Xinjiang , Saya , September 30 , Xinjiang ( Quentin Dan Xiaojun ) - The test base for the cultivation of film @-@ free cotton is located in Saya County , Xinjiang . The growth of film @-@ free cotton is encouraging . Compared to the presence of soil cotton next to it , it is no less colorful . A cluster of snow cotton is in a race to open up . It is full of branches .
From 27 to 28 September , a nationwide film @-@ free cotton field visit and seminar exchange event was held in Saya County , Xinjiang .
During the meeting , the reporter learned that the film @-@ free cotton technology system , which is dominated by domestic cotton 619 and its accompanying cultivation measures , had initially achieved the goal of sedentarization of cotton fields , reduced contamination of the ecological environment and raw cotton by the residues of Xinjiang cotton fields , and made significant progress in the study and demonstration of integrated technology for film @-@ free cotton .
Chinese Academy of Engineering , famous cotton genetics breeders , and Chief Scientist of the national modern agricultural industry technology system , Yu Shuxun , introduced Zhejiang University of Agriculture and Forestry Party Committee Secretary Zhou Guofang @-@ mong on the growth of film @-@ free cotton .
The comprehensive technology we have developed for film @-@ free cotton can completely realize the need to grow cotton without the soil , and can completely solve the problem of contamination of the debris and achieve green cotton planting .
Chinese Academy of Engineering , Yu Shuxun , introduced it .
Xinjiang is the most important cotton @-@ producing region in China . According to the National Bureau of Statistics , the area under cotton cultivation in Xinjiang was 35 million mu in 2017 , accounting for 61 % of the country &apos;s cotton area .
Since the introduction of the topographic film in China in 1982 , the territory of Xinjiang has covered more than 50 million mu of all types of crop cover , using about 300,000 tons of topographic film annually .
Of these , the cotton diaphragm coverage rate reached 100 per cent , with cotton fields covering about 60 per cent of the use of the Xinjiang diaphragm .
The production of non @-@ film cotton is measured , and the production of cotton is completely within reach of 320 kg to 350 kg .
As the amount of land film input in Xinjiang continues to increase , the low rate of recovery of residual land film , the gradual increase in the amount of residual film in the soil and the disruption of soil structure caused by the debris film seriously affect the sustainable development of agriculture .
Paralytic membranes not only cause serious soil contamination but also have a significant impact on the quality of cotton fibres .
At present , over a third of Xinjiang &apos;s cotton fields have been mechanized for harvesting .
In 2017 , the Xinjiang machine cotton mining area was about 14 million mu .
Large quantities of surface and cotton @-@ strapped shredded films are included in the cotton harvesting process , and shredded films doped with raw cotton are difficult to remove during the processing of raw cotton and are not completely removed during subsequent textile processing , seriously affecting the quality of textile products .
On September 28 , a nationwide film @-@ free cotton sightseeing and discussion exchange event was held in Saya County , Xinjiang .
In order to focus on solving the soil pollution in cotton fields , simplifying cotton planting technology and improving cotton field efficiency , Yu Shuxun led his team through eight years to implement the planting of 619 cotton @-@ free films , adding wings to the green development of Xinjiang agriculture .
Yu Shuxun introduced that by innovating new ideas for breeding , he had cultivated an extremely early , saline @-@ resistant , low @-@ temperature , well @-@ produced new line of cotton on the land .
Central cotton 619 wool apos . Under the conditions of seedless cultivation in the southern region of Xinjiang , a series of accompanying measures have been implemented such as seedless seeding mechanics , improved seeding depth , shallow burial of the drip belt under sedentary conditions , suitable seeding density screening , and rational chemical control .
At present , demonstration bases for film @-@ free cotton have been established in Aksu , Kurl and Arar , with a yield of 4,800 kg per hectare .
The planting of cotton without film has resulted in abundant production , savings , environmental protection and improved overall efficiency .
Zhang Donghai , agronomist at the Agricultural Sciences Institute of the Third Division of Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps , said that through nearly six years of research and demonstration on film @-@ free cotton cultivation technology , the production of cotton seeds without film can completely achieve a yield of 320 kg to 350 kg of cotton seeds , and may even be higher .
There are great prospects for the diffusion of seedless cotton cultivation techniques .
Zhang Donghai believes that at present , film @-@ free cotton cultivation technology can completely solve the problem of soil debris contamination , but at present there is a certain gap in economic benefits compared to soil film cultivation .
Support for cotton purchase prices would be beneficial for future marketing .
Yu Shuxun said that next step , he and his team will continue to carry out an in @-@ depth study and widespread application of film @-@ free cotton , strengthen the film @-@ free cotton industry , and thoroughly solve the problem of soil pollution caused by the earth film .
