The reporter learned from the Ministry of Finance on the 30th that the four departments of the Ministry of Finance , the State Administration of Taxation , the State Development Reform Commission , and the Ministry of Commerce recently issued a joint notice that , in order to further encourage overseas investors to invest in China , the profits distributed by overseas investors from resident enterprises in China will be used to temporarily exempt domestic direct investment from the scope of application of the pre @-@ tax income tax policy , and will be extended from foreign investment incentive projects to all projects and areas where foreign investment is not prohibited .
This policy has been implemented since 1 January 2018 .
The notice makes clear that foreign investors &apos; direct investment on a profit @-@ sharing basis includes profit @-@ sharing capital increases , new construction , equity acquisitions and other equity investments by foreign investors , but does not include the addition , transfer or acquisition of shares in listed companies in addition to eligible strategic investments .
Offshore investors who do not actually benefit from the policy of withholding advance income tax may apply to refund the policy and refund the tax paid within three years of the date on which the relevant tax was actually paid .
Moreover , foreign investors may continue to benefit from the policy of withholding the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding of the withholding income tax , if the reorganisation of the invested enterprise meets the special conditions for reorganization and if it is actually being tax @-@ treated in accordance with the special reorganization .
To ensure that profits earned by foreign investors are actually used for direct investment , the notices stipulate that foreign investors &apos; profits for direct investment are paid in cash , that the funds are transferred directly from the account of the profit @-@ distributing enterprise to the account of the investing enterprise or equity @-@ transferring party , and that no other account is subject to turnover within or outside the country prior to direct investment ; that foreign investors &apos; profits for direct investment are paid in kind , marketable securities , etc . , and that ownership of the assets is transferred directly from the profit @-@ distributing enterprise to the investing enterprise or equity @-@ transferring party and cannot be held on behalf of , or temporarily held by , other enterprises or individuals prior to direct investment .
The circular also requires the tax authorities to strengthen their follow @-@ up administration in accordance with the law .
Foreign investors already enjoy a policy of withholding advance income tax payments , and if the required conditions are verified by the subsequent management of the tax administration as not meeting the requirements , except for the allocation of corporate liability for profits , they are considered to have failed to file a corporate income tax declaration in accordance with the requirements , and will be held liable for delayed tax payments , which will be calculated from the date of payment of the related profits .
