A drug previously produced in the Chinese medicine industry was recalled for containing potentially carcinogenic substances .
The European Medicines Agency indicated that further action on other components of the plant &apos;s production was under consideration .
FDA states that it discovered major production process problems during its inspection of pharmaceutical plants in the Hua Sea industry and then stopped importing them .
FDA also states that the import ban will remain in place until the Chinese medicine industry finds out how these impurities will produce and improve its quality control system .
On September 29 , the Chinese medicine industry released a statement on the company &apos;s website , saying : &quot; The company is making a positive attitude and taking vigorous measures to rectify the problems in this official US @-@ European inspection . The company is very surprised and saddened by the way and outcome of this official U.S. @-@ European inspection . &quot;
