inhua News Agency , Fuzhou , October 1 ( Reporter Tai Xiaoan ) On October 1 , the &quot; Regulations on the Safety Management of the Fujian Highway &quot; was officially implemented .
The regulations state that the lifting of kites , balloons , perforated lamps , aircraft and other airborne objects and small aircraft shall be prohibited within 500 meters of each side of the high @-@ speed electrical line conductors .
Provision is made to supplement the prohibitions and restrictions affecting the safety of high @-@ speed railways , to regulate construction and tree planting along high @-@ speed railways , to further clarify the subject matter and scope of supervision of high @-@ speed railways , and to clarify the responsibilities and legal responsibilities for law enforcement and supervision , on the basis of the superior laws such as the Railway Safety Regulations of the People &apos;s Republic of China Law and the geo @-@ climatic characteristics of Fujian province .
The regulations prohibit the lifting of airborne materials and small aircraft such as kites , balloons , Kong Ming lamps , power umbrellas , aircraft , etc . , within 500 meters of each side of the high @-@ speed power line wire , in response to the frequent occurrence of large winds along the coast of Fujian province and the impact on safety of light construction ( construction ) materials and light cargo along the high @-@ speed railway .
In addition , light objects along high @-@ speed railways , such as plastic sheds , colour steel panels , sunscreen masks and light creams such as low @-@ altitude floats and plastic protective films generated during construction , should be protected against harm to the safety of high @-@ speed railways by enhanced protection measures to be taken by all or users .
n response to the characteristics of Fujian Province in hilly areas and high @-@ speed rail tunnels , it is stipulated that railway construction units or railway transport enterprises should be consulted on actions that may affect the safety of the tunnels , including the construction of mountain ponds , reservoirs , dams , digging of rivers , drainage channels , drilling of wells , etc . , within 200 meters of each side of the center line above the high @-@ speed rail tunnels .
At the same time , those responsible for violating the provisions of the Regulations will be ordered to correct them by the public security organs ; if the circumstances are more serious , they will be punished by a fine not exceeding RMB 50 million and a fine not exceeding RMB 200 million and a fine not exceeding RMB 500 million ; if the circumstances are serious , they will be punished by a fine not exceeding RMB 10,000 to 30,000 and a fine not exceeding RMB 500 million .
Where damage has been caused , liability shall be established by law .
ccording to reports , with the rapid development of railway construction , the speed of the high @-@ speed railway in Fujian province at 200 kilometers per hour and above has now reached 1516 kilometers . It has achieved a city bus , and is expected to reach 2,150 kilometers per hour in Fujian and above in the next five years .
The implementation of this provision will standardize the safety management of high @-@ speed railways in Fujian province , further implement the responsibilities of local government departments , integrate railways with local forces , work together to safeguard high @-@ speed railway safety , and improve the safety and control system of high @-@ speed railways in Fujian province .
