The number of people killed or as many as several thousand killed in the aftermath of the strong earthquake tsunami in Indonesia @ - @ CNS
According to the comprehensive report , a 7.5 @-@ magnitude shallow earthquake struck Surawesi Island , Indonesia , on 28 September , triggering a 6 @-@ metre tsunami .
The National Disaster Response Agency announced on 30 September that the number of deaths had increased to 832 , mainly in the capital , Palu , and in Donggara district adjacent to the epicentre of the earthquake .
Vice @-@ President Kara noted that , as the number of casualties in some of the affected areas remained uncalculated , the number of fatalities could be as high as thousands .
The strong earthquake in Central Sulawesi Province , Indonesia , on the afternoon of 28 September , and the tsunami that triggered it have resulted in 832 deaths .
2.4 million people affected by the collapse of thousands of buildings
As a result of the devastation that followed the Palu disaster , thousands of buildings collapsed and several roads were broken , according to the authorities , an estimated 2.4 million people were affected .
A hotel on the local coast collapsed , with only 24 guests escaping safely and an estimated 50 to 60 people trapped in rubble , with occasional calls for help , and relief workers successfully rescued a young woman on 30 September .
The authorities have been unable to use heavy machinery to remove rubble and have been slow in the search and rescue process because of the need to ensure the safety of those trapped .
A shopping mall also collapsed in the city , where hundreds of residents rushed to wait for news from relatives and friends .
Many residents used social platforms to send messages in search of separated relatives and friends .
On September 30 , local time , a hotel collapsed and relief work began in the Indonesian city of Central Sulawesi Baru .
The whereabouts of 10 thousand persons in Palu awaiting rescue : 5 foreigners
According to the authorities , some 10,000 people are waiting to be rescued in Palu city , scattered across 50 locations .
At the time of the earthquake , 71 foreigners were known to be in Palu , of whom 66 were temporarily known to be safe , including 21 Chinese citizens , while the whereabouts of the remaining two French , two Malaysian tourists and one Korean were unknown .
The Chinese Embassy in Indonesia is seeking to verify the situation of Chinese citizens in the affected areas through various channels and has not yet received reports of casualties among Chinese citizens .
Communications in Donggara district , near the epicentre of the earthquake , remained suspended and 11 people were temporarily informed of their deaths , but no further details were available .
According to scene images , coastal areas and ports in Donggara county were severely damaged , a large number of buildings were rolled away , bodies were scattered and Red Cross rescue teams were travelling to the area for search and rescue .
Indonesian President &apos;s inspection of the disaster situation said that reconstruction work would begin as soon as possible
The roads in Palu and Donggara were severely damaged , and on 30 September the Palu airport opened for use only by aircraft transporting relief supplies , allowing relief supplies and personnel to arrive as soon as possible and to evacuate seriously injured persons .
Many of the local hospitals are still without electricity and the wounded are being treated outside the home .
More than 10,000 people were in reception centres , and some feared that the aftershocks would not dare to go home , preferring to stay outdoors overnight .
Following the collapse of the Palu prison in the earthquake , which led to the escape of hundreds of prisoners , more than 100 prisoners in Donggara county also escaped during the chaos caused by the earthquake , and prisoners set fire to disturbances in detention centres .
The President of Indonesia , Joko , visited Palu on 30 September and stated that it was very difficult to resolve a large number of problems in a short period of time , including the resumption of communications .
He appealed to the affected population for patience and said that the authorities would begin the reconstruction process as soon as possible .
On the other hand , the Minister of Finance of Indonesia announced that the Government had allocated 560 billion Indonesian guilders for disaster relief .
One confirmed case of H5N6 bird flu infection in Guangdong Province
According to the latest report from the Mainland Department of Health , Guangdong Province confirmed one case of a person infected with H5N6 bird flu .
The Department calls on the population to avoid exposure to birds and to pay attention to personal and food hygiene .
According to the information , the patient is a 22 @-@ year @-@ old man and currently resides in Bai Yun District , Guangzhou City , Guangdong Province . Due to symptoms such as fever on September 25 , he was admitted to hospital for treatment on September 26 and is currently being treated in isolation in the hospital .
Patients were slaughtered and eaten live poultry before they became sick .
Since April 2014 , there have been confirmed cases of H5N6 bird flu in Sichuan , Guangdong , Yunnan , Hubei , Hunan , Anhui and Guangxi Gang Autonomous Regions .
The Department of Health is in close contact with the national and neighbouring health departments and the World Health Organization ( WHO ) on a continuous basis to closely monitor the epidemic in various localities and Australia .
To prevent human exposure to avian flu , the Health Bureau calls the attention of the public to the following matters :
Avoid exposure to poultry birds or their secrets , excreta ; if there is exposure , wash hands immediately ;
Do not buy and carry unquarantined birds ;
Do not eat bird meat , visceral , blood products and eggs that are not fully cooked ;
Pay attention to personal hygiene and often wash hands ;
If symptoms such as fever , cough and breathing difficulties arise , they should wear masks and seek medical attention as soon as possible , and give doctors detailed information on travel history and animal exposure history .
