Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said in a speech to the US Foreign Relations Commission on Friday that the Sino @-@ US relationship is now once again at a crossroads , and that if the two sides can take a positive and inclusive view of each other , expand their positive cooperation , and properly manage their differences , they can open up better prospects .
Sino @-@ American relations are our common asset and need our mutual protection .
He expressed the hope that intelligent people from all walks of life in the two countries would take concrete action to maintain the healthy and stable development of Sino @-@ US relations and jointly push the Sino @-@ US relations in the right direction .
Wang Yi also re @-@ emphasized that China will definitely take a different development path from that of the traditional great powers .
This path , which has Chinese characteristics , determines that China will not and cannot repeat the mistakes of being a hegemon of the powerful and powerful . It also determines that China will neither become the United States , will not challenge the United States , and will not replace the United States .
In his speech entitled &quot; Opportunities or Challenges , Partners or Counterparties , &quot; Wang Yi said that the deeper problem with the current problem lies in the fact that some American friends believe that China will also dominate the country and even challenge and replace America &apos;s leadership position in the world .
This is clearly a major strategic miscalculation .
According to him , however , this self @-@ imagined suspicion is spreading , exacerbating existing contradictions , creating new ones , and making it more difficult and difficult to solve specific problems between China and the US .
Wang Yi pointed out that China follows a path of peaceful development .
The Chinese have never had the genes for external expansion .
