South Korea &apos;s exports fell the largest year @-@ on @-@ year since July 2016 , by 5.7 % more than predicted by the Reuters survey &apos;s 11 analysts .
The initial value released on Monday showed that exports in September were $ 50.6 billion , down from $ 51.2 billion in August .
South Korea &apos;s exports to China grew by 7.8 % in September , for the twenty @-@ third consecutive month , despite concerns that growing US @-@ China trade disputes could hurt other export @-@ dependent Chinese neighbors as well .
South Korea &apos;s exports to the United States fell by 11.8 per cent , owing to a decline in the sale of petroleum products .
South Korea &apos;s memory chip and oil product sales abroad increased by 28.3 % and 13.5 % , respectively , despite market concerns that the so @-@ called chip super @-@ cycle may have peaked .
The impact of the trade conflict will be inevitable , however , as South Korea relies heavily on the US and Chinese markets for its exports .
Imports declined by between 2.1 per cent and $ 40.8 billion , which is less than the 3.1 per cent increase estimated in the Reuters survey .
The initial trade surplus in September was $ 9.7 billion , up from $ 6.9 billion in August .
According to the Ministry of Industry , as a result of the US and EU countries , global manufacturing will remain robust , which is a beneficial factor for South Korean exports .
he statement pointed out that the increase in export prices caused by the rise in oil prices will also benefit exports in the second half of this year .
The continuation of the trade conflict between the United States and China , coupled with increased market volatility following the US interest rate hike , are all negative pressures on exports .
Exports increased from an average of $ 2.6 billion per working day in September to $ 2.1 billion in August .
