China News Agency , Fuzhou , September 30 ( Reporter Long Min ) -- The Sixth Meeting of the Thirteenth People &apos;s Congress Standing Committee of Fujian Province voted on the 30th to adopt the Regulations on Promotion of Ecological Civilization in Fujian Province .
Green Qingshan is the first time that Jinshan Silver Mountain has been incorporated into the legislation of Fujian Province , making it an operational and enforceable provision throughout the regulations .
Fujian is China &apos;s first national ecological civilization test area .
The head of the legal system office of the People &apos;s Government of Fujian Province said that it was necessary and urgent to form a basic law on the construction of ecological civilization from a holistic and holistic perspective in order to solve the problem of regulating the construction of ecological civilization through separate regulations and policy documents , and also to provide a legal basis for the enactment of relevant regulations , normative documents and measures .
This regulation fully embodies the characteristics of Fujian and translates mature experience in the practice of building ecological civilization into a form of regulations and their implementation : for example , the reproducible and replicable experience of soil and water conservation and management in Fujian Province , and the regulations summarize and upgrade the experience of soil and water conservation and management in Fujian Province , stipulating that local people &apos;s governments above county level should strengthen their unified leadership of soil and water conservation and define priority prevention and control areas based on the results of soil erosion surveys , etc . ; also , for example , the river system that started in Fujian Province , the regulations elevate the river system and the lake system to the legislative level , stipulating that local people &apos;s governments at all levels should fully implement river and lake management , and implement river lake management bodies , responsibilities and funding .
The regulation provides for a life @-@ long accountability system for ecological damage .
Those who violate the requirements of scientific development and cause serious damage to ecological resources are held accountable for their entire lives for leading cadres and related officials .
t is said that the Regulations for the Promotion of Ecological Civilization in Fujian Province will be implemented on November 1 this year .
China and Pakistan agreed to complete the construction of the economic corridor in time to accelerate the construction of the port of Gwadar
The Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs said on Sunday that China and Pakistan agreed to further consolidate and expand their economic relations .
China and Pakistan issued a joint statement on Sunday to further strengthen the strategic partnership .
Both sides reiterated their commitment to building the Sino @-@ Palestinian economic corridor and rejected the negative propaganda against the Sino @-@ Palestinian economic corridor .
Reuters quoted the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs as saying that China and Pakistan will strengthen practical cooperation in the area of trade and investment and upgrade Pakistan &apos;s industrial capabilities by establishing joint ventures in priority areas , transferring labor @-@ intensive industries , and developing SME cooperation .
According to a press release published on the website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs , the two sides agreed to complete the ongoing construction of the China @-@ Pakistan economic corridor in a timely manner , accelerate the construction of the port of Gwadar and ancillary projects , focus on economic and social development , job creation and livelihood improvement , and accelerate cooperation in industry and parks and agriculture .
The two sides also agreed to complete the second phase of the Sino @-@ Palestinian FTA negotiations as soon as possible and to continue the Sino @-@ Palestinian services trade agreement negotiations .
In a joint statement signed on Sunday , the two sides reaffirmed their commitment to the construction of the Sino @-@ Palestinian economic corridor , which they agreed would be a cooperative win @-@ win plan that would promote regional connectivity and bring prosperity and development to the entire region .
The two sides agreed that the port of Gwadar was an important node for cross @-@ regional connectivity and a pillar of the China @-@ Pakistan economic corridor .
Both sides agreed to accelerate the construction of the port of Gwadar and ancillary projects .
In a joint statement , China and Pakistan also expressed their opposition to negative propaganda targeting the economic corridor between China and Palestine .
Both sides agreed to establish the Sino @-@ Palestinian Foreign Minister &apos;s Strategic Dialogue and to restructure the former Deputy Foreign Minister &apos;s Strategic Dialogue into diplomatic consultations .
In addition , the two countries will further strengthen their defence cooperation by maintaining high @-@ level visits between the military forces of the two countries and exchanges between departments and levels .
In order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China , the Ministry of Finance and other four ministries jointly announced that , as of 1 January 2018 , the scope of application of the policy of withholding pre @-@ tax revenues for domestic direct investment on profits distributed by foreign investors from resident enterprises in China would be extended from foreign investment incentive projects to all non @-@ prohibited foreign investment projects and areas .
The Ministry of Finance website published a related notice stating that foreign investors are temporarily exempted from pre @-@ tax collection subject to several conditions , including foreign investors &apos; direct investment in profits , including foreign investors &apos; return on profits , new construction , equity acquisitions and other equity investments , but not including the addition , transfer and acquisition of shares in listed companies ( except for eligible strategic investments ) .
It also includes dividends and dividends earned by foreign investors as equity returns resulting from the actual distribution of realized retained earnings to investors by resident enterprises in China .
If the profits of the foreign investor for direct investment are paid in cash , the relevant funds are transferred directly from the account of the profit @-@ distributing enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or equity transferor and may not be transferred to other accounts within or outside the country prior to direct investment ; if the profits of the foreign investor for direct investment are paid in kind , marketable securities and other non @-@ cash forms , ownership of the assets is transferred directly from the profit @-@ distributing enterprise to the invested enterprise or equity transferor , prior to direct investment , is not held by other enterprises or individuals on their behalf or temporarily .
The notice added that foreign investors actually reclaim their direct investment that is subject to the withholding of the advance income tax policy through equity transfers , repurchase , liquidation , etc . , and file a refund of the deferred tax with the tax authorities within seven days of the actual receipt of the corresponding amount in accordance with the established procedure .
In order to encourage foreign investors to continue investing in China , the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Commerce jointly issued a circular at the end of 2017 stating that , with effect from 1 January 2017 , no advance income tax will be levied on foreign investors &apos; profits distributed from resident enterprises in China and invested directly in incentive @-@ type investment projects , if they meet the required conditions .
Last week , the Standing Committee of the State Council of China decided to further strengthen intellectual property protection by extending the application of the moratorium on pre @-@ tax collection on foreign reinvestment from incentive @-@ based foreign investment projects to all non @-@ prohibited projects and areas .
The reporter learned from the National Health Commission that the incidence of child malnutrition in our country has decreased compared to decades ago , while the incidence of overweight obesity has increased significantly .
Experts pointed out in this regard that the most important concept for maintaining healthy body weight is to fight the disease and vigorously promote scientific fitness and reasonable diets .
According to the Core Information and Interpretation for Adolescent Health Education in China ( 2018 edition ) recently released by the National Health and Hygiene Committee , the key to maintaining healthy body weight is rational diets and scientific sports .
Excessive weight , obesity , and blind weight loss are not good for health .
The underlying health problems behind the stomach of obesity cannot be ignored .
Ding Steel , Director of the Nutrition and Health Institute of China &apos;s Centers for Disease Prevention and Control , said that overweight obesity jeopardizes the normal growth and development of adolescents , adversely affects their psychology , behaviour , cognition and intelligence , and can even lead to high blood pressure , hyperglycemia and hyperlipid in children .
At the same time , overweight obesity among adolescents can easily continue into adulthood , increasing the risk of chronic diseases such as hypertension and diabetes among adolescents as adults .
Ding Steel said that the 2010 @ - @ 2012 testing of the nutritional and health status of Chinese residents showed that our country &apos;s 6 @ - @ 17 @-@ year @-@ old children had an excess weight rate of 9.6 per cent and an obesity rate of 6.4 per cent , which together was 16 per cent .
At the same time , overweight obesity among young children tends to be higher among boys than girls and higher in urban areas than in rural areas , with overweight obesity rates increasing markedly in recent decades .
How do adolescents respond to overweight obesity ?
Zhang Yan , deputy director of the Scientific Physical Fitness and Health Promotion Research Centre of the State Sports Administration , pointed out that the main reason for obesity among adolescents at present is excessive calorie intake and inadequate physical activity .
For this singular obesity , emphasis should be placed on scientific exercise combined with sound dietary control .
Zhang Yan pointed out that the most important concept for maintaining healthy weight is to fight the disease . One important part of this is to provide comprehensive science education to schools , parents and students , popularize the dangers of overweight and obesity , and raise the awareness of adolescents about prevention .
Adolescents should undergo regular medical examinations to monitor growth and development indicators such as high body weight , early detection , scientific judgement and obesity for timely intervention .
For adolescents who are already overweight obese , Ding and Steel recommend that they be at a special physiological stage , except for active scientific arrangements for meals and exercise , that they avoid using starvation or semi @-@ starvation therapy to control and reduce body weight , and that they refrain from blind use of fertilizers .
