The first phase of the mausoleum project covered more than 2,000 square meters and consisted of the indelible monument of the heroes , the heroes of the war of resistance , the mausoleums , etc .
The Mausoleum , the hero of the resistance war , provided the Hsiang war heroes with a tomb behind their backs free of charge and was praised as the last military barracks of the veterans of the resistance war .
Every year , before and after Qing Ming and National Day , the mausoleum holds large @-@ scale public sacrifices and burial ceremonies .
Since 2015 , seven collective burial ceremonies for war veterans have been held here , where 102 war veterans and partners have been sleeping .
Xinhua News Agency , Yichang , October 1 ( Guo Xiaoying , Liu Min ) - The newly revised &quot; Three Gorges @ - @ Gücontinent Dam Hydropower Hub Traffic Control Protocol &quot; ( hereinafter referred to as &quot; Movement Control Protocol &quot; ) officially began implementation on October 1 . Two years after the three Gorges lift machine was piloted , the three Gorges officially unified with the trip gates .
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations , the three isthmus @ - @ gymnasium dam waters were navigated in good order .
The Changjiang Three Gorges Navigation Authority issued its first security inspection plan at 2100 hours on 30 September and conducted security inspections of 160 vessels , a total of 124 of which were certified .
At 1400 hours on 1 October , the Department of Navigation arranged for the first pass @-@ through plan after the implementation of the new regulations .
Following the implementation of the new regulations , the security inspection plan was issued once a day at 0900 and 2100 hours , and the dam plan was issued once a day at 1400 and 2000 hours , respectively , to facilitate flexible arrangements by ships for the dam plan .
The Movement Control Protocol added the principle of sorting and controlling the movement of dams across ships , specifying the priority of dams on the basis of the functional positioning of gates and lifts , respectively , and adjusting short @-@ line passenger vessels through gates to the same priority level as demonstration ships and honest ships .
This is also the second anniversary of the pilot operation of the lift , and it is officially scheduled in unison with the stop .
And for the first time , the Kawaguang River and the Three Gorges Area have also been given priority by large @-@ sized , broad @-@ sized demonstration boats and new energy @-@ powered boats .
At the same time , the Movement Control Protocol adjusted the waters of the Route Movement Control and Management from the previous 180 kilometers of nearby dams to 541.8 kilometers of waters of the Yunyang Yangtze River Bridge to the Shijiang River Bridge , and divided the waters of the core , nearby dams , controlled waters , and dispatch waters .
This facilitates the choice of suitable waters to be blocked and reduces the backlog of ships to be blocked in the dam area .
The Movement Control Protocol also proposes good faith measures such as cancelling declarations on non @-@ compliant ships and delaying dams by 24 hours , based on the characteristics of existing ships &apos; dams and gates .
The storage of water in the Three Gorges resulted in improved navigation conditions in the storage area , which facilitated the rapid development of navigation on the Yangtze River .
The data show that the annual cargo throughput of the three isthmus and the Ground Dam increased from 34.3 million tons in 2004 to 138 million tons and 140 million tons in 2017 , respectively .
In the past two years , the three isthmus lifts have tried traffic through 5,767 vessels , 162,200 passengers and 1,712,800 tons of cargo .
Chen Wanyuan , Deputy Director of the Three Gorges Traffic Management Authority , said that the Movement Control Regulations had a positive effect on promoting honest pass management , maintaining traffic order at the two dams &apos; hubs , dispelling the pressure on vessels waiting to be blocked in the dams area , and improving traffic capacity .
