Sept . 30 , Reuters - On Sunday , the China Securities Regulatory Commission officially released the revised &quot; Guidelines on Corporate Governance in Listed Stock . &quot; The focus of this revision includes further strengthening restrictions on controlling shareholders , actual controllers and their related parties , focusing more on the protection of small and medium @-@ sized investors , and playing the role of small and medium @-@ sized investors protection agency . At the same time , it is actively drawing on international experience to promote the participation of institutional investors in corporate governance .
The Commission noted that the revised guidelines covered the basic concepts and principles of corporate governance in listed companies , the composition and functioning of shareholders &apos; assemblies , boards of directors and supervisory boards , the rights and obligations of directors , supervisors and senior managers , incentives and discipline for listed companies , and the conduct of controlling shareholders and their related parties .
The new guidelines also include the participation of institutional investors and related institutions in corporate governance , the basic requirements of listed companies in terms of stakeholders , environmental protection and social responsibility , and information disclosure and transparency .
The revised guidelines require listed companies to implement innovative , coordinated , green , open and shared development concepts in corporate governance , increase the party @-@ building requirements of listed companies and strengthen the leading role of listed companies in environmental protection and social responsibility .
Strengthen the role of the Board &apos;s Audit Committee and establish a basic framework for environmental , social responsibility and corporate governance ( ESG ) disclosure .
In addition , in response to concerns , the new guidelines introduced new requirements for control stability in the governance of listed companies , the performance of independent directors , high evaluation and incentive restraint mechanisms for directors of listed companies , and enhanced disclosure of information .
The Commission also noted that , in accordance with the new standards , it would study the improvement of relevant regulations and normative documents , guide stock exchanges , the China Association of Listed Companies and other self @-@ regulatory organizations in the development and revision of relevant self @-@ regulatory rules , and gradually improve the system of rules for the governance of listed companies .
At the same time , the training of listed companies has been strengthened , the voluntary nature of listed companies in improving their governance and regularizing their operations has been strengthened , and the quality of listed companies has been continuously improved .
