Expanding imports is not a matter of equity , but a long @-@ term perspective for the future , with Chinese imports of goods and services expected to exceed $ 30 trillion and $ 10 trillion , respectively , over the next 15 years .
In his keynote address at China &apos;s first International Import Expo , Xi Jinping said that China will further reduce tariffs , accelerate the development of new industries such as cross @-@ border electronics , continuously liberalize market access , promote service @-@ sector liberalization , and ease restrictions on foreign @-@ equity ratios in areas such as education and health care , where domestic markets are in large gaps .
