The number of deaths from the strong earthquake and tsunami in Indonesia rose to 420 , and no Chinese citizen casualties have been reported
ccording to figures released by Wilem Rampangilei , head of the Indonesian Disaster Response Agency , Indonesia &apos;s official news agency , the number of people killed by the strong earthquake and tsunami in Central Sulawesi Province of Indonesia rose to 420 at midnight on the 29th .
According to the official , this is only statistics for the municipality of Palu , the capital of Central Sulawesi province , and does not include the Denggara district , where the earthquake hit , and the nearby Sigi area , where communications are still suspended and the number of people killed has not yet been reported .
Search and rescue efforts have been very difficult owing to the severe damage to many roads in the city of Palu and the inaccessibility of heavy machinery .
In order to guarantee the rescue , the closed Palu airport , which began to open late on the 28th , stopped all commercial flights on the evening of 29th , and the flight of the journalist from Jakarta to Palu , which had been booked that evening , was cancelled .
Immediately after the earthquake and tsunami , the Chinese Embassy in Indonesia sought information from various sources to verify the situation of Chinese citizens in the affected areas .
To date , no casualties among Chinese citizens have been reported .
