Misrepresentations such as the so @-@ called private economy &apos;s disengagement theory , the new public @-@ private partnership theory , etc . , have aroused misgivings and anxiety among some entrepreneurs .
Recently , a number of private enterprises have encountered difficulties and problems in the development of their businesses .
For example , changes in the international economic environment have had an impact on some exporting enterprises ; rapid adjustment of the demand structure has brought about transformational escalation pressures ; and some policies have been inconsistent , with overlapping policy effects or simplistic working methods that have led to the counterproductive effects of otherwise well @-@ intended policies .
A combination of factors had led to difficulties in the private economy , difficulties in the operation of some private enterprises and considerable anxiety among entrepreneurs .
Against this background , it is particularly relevant to correct misconceptions , unload the minds of entrepreneurs , and let enterprises concentrate on development , and the government concentrate on development , which is about market confidence and development expectations .
