The symposium even more clearly proposed a series of practical measures to support the development and growth of private enterprises in six areas , and put forward a series of practical actions to work with private enterprises .
These are extremely encouraging for the entrepreneurial community and give rise to greater expectations from all sectors of society .
When the fog is out and the approach is decided , the key is to implement it .
It is necessary to continuously create a better development environment for the private economy , help private enterprises solve the difficulties of development , and help upgrade China &apos;s economic transformation ; it is necessary to give entrepreneurs a sense of fairness in market competition , safety in their legitimate business , respect in social life , and stimulate innovation and creative potential .
As China &apos;s economy moves into a process of high @-@ quality development , it needs more entrepreneurial ambitions and offers more space and space for entrepreneurial creativity .
We have reason to believe that , with deeper reforms and the removal of obstacles , the private economy will open up better prospects for development and development towards a broader stage .
All 46 regulatory certificates in the Inner Mongolia import and export chain are online verified - China News Network
Chinanews.com , Howe , November 5 ( Reporter Li Eiping ) - Howe Customs said on the 5th that from now on , all 46 regulatory certificates in the local import and export chain will be online verified , except for special circumstances such as confidentiality needs .
Inner Mongolian enterprises can declare relevant documents to Customs on a paperless basis , avoiding problems such as previous on @-@ site travel , paper applications , repeated submission , etc .
It was understood that document preparation time , which refers to the preparation time of the various types of documents required for the import / export chain before the declaration of customs , was a major factor affecting the overall clearance time , which had to be reduced if customs clearance time was to be reduced and customs clearance costs reduced .
The number of regulatory documents previously subject to customs inspection in the import and export chain amounted to 86 , covering 19 departments .
It is reported that this time , in accordance with the principle of cancelling it , merging it , withdrawing from the port inspection and checking it , and relying on the international trade single window inspection platform , customs and 16 other licensing agencies system docking and interconnecting the data , it has achieved more data runways and fewer business runs .
According to the customs department , in the past , enterprises had to send paper applications back and forth to and from the office hall of the relevant department . The process was long and the approval status could not be tracked in real time .
Enterprise users now have direct access to the Single Window portal for online applications .
After the approval of the certification department , the electronic data transmission of the certificate to the customs office is carried out , and automatic matching and intelligent verification of customs clearance data is achieved at the customs clearance stage . The results of the inspection are uniformly fed back to enterprises through a single window , and the entire process of regulating document declaration , clearance , customs clearance and feedback is implemented online .
South Korean ginseng Chicken soup &apos;s exports to China have jumped 20 @-@ fold in 4 years or are related to an increase in the number of young people in the empty nest @ - @ China News Network
Analysis of the steep 20 @-@ fold increase in South Korea &apos;s Chicken soup exports to China in 4 years : related to the increase in the number of young people in empty nesting
South Korea News Agency reported on the 5th that South Korean ginseng soup exported more than US $ 100,000 to China last year , a sharp increase of about 20 times from 2013 , four years ago .
According to the analysis , this increase is related to the increase in the number of young people in China &apos;s empty nesting , the introduction of convenient food hot marketing , and the increased interest of young people in feeding .
The data were published on the 5th by the Korean Agro @-@ Aquaculture Circulation Commune ( aT ) .
Last year , South Korean ginseng soup exported $ 103.39 million to China , weighing 218.59 million kilograms , a sharp increase of 2094 per cent and 3668.8 per cent over 2013 , respectively .
According to the analysis , the increase in sales of Korean ginseng chicken soup in China is related to the increase in the number of young people in empty nesting leading to convenient food hot marketing , and the increased attention of young people to nutritious meals .
As of this year , households in China have surpassed the 200 million mark and are expected to increase to 30 % of the population by 2020 . Local food enterprises are also targeting all kinds of convenient foods .
In addition , the analysis also indicated that avian flu is the biggest factor preventing ginseng chicken soup from taking root in the mainland Chinese market .
aT said that from November 2016 to April last year , an avian flu epidemic occurred in South Korea , and the relevant departments banned all exports of ginseng soup to China , resulting in a sharp decline in exports .
Exports of ginseng soup to China in 2016 amounted to $ 0.84 million , and last year exports plummeted to $ 0.1 million due to avian flu .
