WASHINGTON , November 5 - On Monday , the United States renewed its sanctions on Iran &apos;s oil and financial sectors , putting increased pressure on Iran to limit its missile and nuclear programs and contain Iran &apos;s growing military and political influence in the Middle East .
Such a move would restore the sanctions lifted by the United States under the 2015 Iran nuclear agreement and add 300 additional targets for Iranian oil , shipping , insurance and banking .
Details of the sanctions will be published at a press conference of 1330 GMT by Secretary of State Mike Pompeo and Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin .
The United States indicated that it would temporarily allow the continued purchase of Iranian oil in eight importing locations , including major Iranian oil buyers such as China , India , South Korea , Japan and Turkey , to ensure stable crude oil prices .
United States officials indicated that those countries would deposit the funds paid to Iran in a trust account .
