A flag @-@ raising ceremony at the border crossing between China and Vietnam to celebrate the National Day
Unexpectedly , there was such a strong and spectacular flag @-@ raising ceremony on the border , which was even more shocking than watching the flag @-@ raising ceremony in the interior .
On the morning of the 1st , Mr. Zhang , who traveled from Sichuan to the Yunnan river port on the Chinese @-@ Vietnamese border , together with more than 500 troops , residents , and Chinese and foreign tourists watched the flag @-@ raising ceremony to celebrate the 69th anniversary of the founding of the People &apos;s Republic of China .
The Haikou crossing is the largest port in the Yunnan section of the border between China and Vietnam . It is located in Hongkou County , Hongzhou Province of Yunnan Province . It is a border crossing with the Old Street City of Viet Nam and belongs to the category of the State .
As the construction of the national border crossing continues to deepen , as one of China &apos;s easiest access routes to Southeast Asia , the flow of entry and exit at the estuarine has steadily increased .
At 7 : 30 a.m. that same day , the sun just revealed a corner , and the locals at the estuaries of the river and Chinese and foreign tourists gathered early in the restricted area of the estuaries to watch the flag @-@ raising ceremony .
At 0745 hours , the flag @-@ raising ceremony began punctually , and members of the national garrison at the border checkpoint at Kawaguchi made a jittery and escorted the national flag to the flag @-@ raising platform at an orthotic pace .
After the commander gave the order to raise the flag , the flag @-@ taker strove to draw an arc with his arms , and the magnificent five @-@ star red flag was generally comfortable with the flag , accompanied by a slow rise in the strong and strong rhythm of the national anthem .
Holding flag @-@ raising ceremonies on the occasion of each New Year &apos;s Day , Spring Festival , National Day , etc . , is not only a demonstration of China &apos;s image , it can also inspire patriotic sentiment among the people of all ethnic groups on the border .
The officers and soldiers of the Soldier Corps who participated in this flag @-@ raising ceremony said so .
According to reports , the national gate garrison responsible for the flag @-@ raising ceremony at the estuarine is composed of more than 40 officers and soldiers from various positions at the border checkpoint at the estuarine , from a flag @-@ raising team of three to a large garrison . The garrison has gone through more than 60 years of history and has carried out more than 70 ceremonial missions to foreign affairs activities at the national level since its formation .
The newly revised Personal Income Tax Act adjusted China &apos;s personal income tax resident tax determination criteria from one year to 183 days .
Relevant officials of the Ministry of Finance of China and the State Administration of Taxation said on the 30th that , in order to maintain policy stability , the next step in implementing the new personal income tax law will be to consider continuing preferential arrangements for overseas persons , including Hong Kong , Macau and Taiwan .
The person in charge said that the current regulations on the implementation of the personal income tax law have special privileges for foreign persons . Individuals who do not have a domicile in China but have resided for more than one year or five years may pay personal income tax only for those parts of the income earned outside China that are paid by units or individuals in China .
The portion paid abroad is not subject to personal income tax in China .
The Ministry of Finance of China , the State Administration of Taxation , the State Development and Reform Commission and the Ministry of Commerce have also issued circulars expanding the scope of application of the policy of withholding advance income tax from foreign investors for the purpose of allocating profits for direct investment .
The distribution of profits among foreign investors from resident enterprises in China has been extended from foreign investment incentive projects to all projects and areas where foreign investment is not prohibited , to the policy of not imposing a pre @-@ tax on domestic direct investment .
During the 73rd session of the United Nations General Assembly , some positive messages were released on the Korean peninsula .
South Korean President Moon Jae @-@ un remarked on North Korea &apos;s irreversible nuclear renunciation and said that US President Donald Trump and North Korea &apos;s top leader , Kim Jong @-@ un , could meet before the end of this year .
The United States Department of State later said that Secretary of State Pompeo would visit North Korea in October to advance the implementation of the United States and North Korean leaders &apos; Singapore commitments .
From the beginning of this year to the present , North Korea and South Korea have broken the hard ice and opened the way for dialogue . The leaders of North Korea and North Korea and the United States have met , the general trend of easing the situation on the peninsula has continued , and the principle of dialogue to resolve the issue on the peninsula has been upheld .
First , the essence of the issue of the peninsula is that the issue of security remains unchanged and peace on the peninsula is achieved . The key is to address the legitimate security concerns of all parties in a proper and balanced manner , instead of insisting on putting pressure on the other side and insisting on one &apos;s own demands .
Secondly , in the dialogue on achieving the denuclearization of the peninsula , the parties concerned are still divided on the steps and modalities for achieving the denuclearization of the peninsula . Due to the long @-@ standing lack of political trust between North Korea and the United States , the game thinking about who will first come after whom remains strong .
At the open meeting of the Security Council on the Korean peninsula held recently at United Nations Headquarters in New York , different voices around the issue of sanctions against the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Korea once again highlighted these two points .
United States Secretary of State Pompeo insisted that sanctions against North Korea would not be lifted until the Korean peninsula was completely denuclearized .
Russian Foreign Minister Lavrov , for his part , emphasized the principle of responding with action , arguing that the weakening trend of sanctions should be the same as North Korea &apos;s progress toward nuclear disarmament .
There is no doubt that the parties concerned should continue to implement the Council &apos;s resolution on the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Korea in a comprehensive , complete and accurate manner , but pressure is not an end in itself , and the implementation of sanctions and the promotion of a political solution are both required by the Council &apos;s resolutions .
As Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said , given the current positive developments in inter @-@ Korean relations with the United States , China believes that it is necessary for the Security Council to consider launching reversible provisions in due course , thus encouraging North Korea and all parties concerned to take greater steps towards denuclearization .
Looking back , the denuclearization of the peninsula and every progress in the peace process will require sufficient political courage on all sides .
At the present time , in the face of the growing expectations of the international community to move forward with a political solution to the issue of the peninsula , the parties concerned should , in particular , demonstrate political courage , make political determinations , implement their commitments , resolve difficult issues and continue to move in a step @-@ by @-@ step manner to advance the denuclearization process of the peninsula in parallel with the establishment of the peace regime on the peninsula and jointly usher in a permanent peace on the peninsula .
