Provision of influenza vaccination services in health centres and health posts , especially during the National Day holiday
This year , the Health Bureau ordered 150,000 doses of flu vaccine 2018 @ - @ 2019 . At this stage , priority is given to providing free vaccinations to high @-@ risk people . To facilitate residents &apos; holidays , the Health Centres and Health Stations under the Health Bureau provide vaccination services from 9 a.m. to 1 noon , especially during the National Day holiday ( October 1 and 2 ) .
In addition to the above @-@ mentioned convenience measures , since the introduction of the plan , the health centres and health posts under the Health Bureau have extended the vaccination service on Monday to Friday to 8 p.m. and 4,158 people were vaccinated by 4 p.m. on September 30 , up from 3,714 in the same period last year .
The free vaccinations are intended for residents of Macao as follows : persons aged 6 months to under 18 , persons aged 50 and over , pregnant women , all chronically ill persons , including obese persons ( i.e. persons with a physical quality index BMI of 30 or above ) , as well as staff of residential homes , nurseries , kindergartens , primary and secondary schools , all health workers , and Macao residents working in the lottery .
At the same time , other persons deemed necessary by the Health Service , including the public sector , will be vaccinated by health centres upon their own initiative in contacting the relevant agencies to obtain the list .
In order to facilitate vaccinations and reduce waiting times , between October and December this year , the HB will send medical personnel to our own secondary schools , primary schools , kindergartens and nurseries to provide group vaccinations for young children , small and medium @-@ sized children , teachers and employees , etc . In addition , the HB will arrange group vaccinations for the elderly and handicapped , the larger number of public sector or other institutions , etc .
Students and young children who fail to take part in group vaccinations may be vaccinated on December 3 , 2018 at the inoculation station or health center of Queen &apos;s Bench Hospital with a Macao resident identity card , a health service user card , an influenza vaccination card ( if any ) , a student certificate , an employee &apos;s certificate , or a career document .
The Bureau reminded residents that between September 2017 and August 2018 , those who had received influenza vaccine from 2017 to 2018 would still need to receive a new dose of influenza vaccine starting in September 2018 , and that influenza antigen content in the Northern Hemisphere influenza vaccine was updated for 2018 @ - @ 2019 , targeting the Northern Hemisphere 2018 @ - @ 2019 winter and summer 2019 seasonal influenza .
The peak flu season in Macao generally occurs between January and March of each year , later than in temperate regions ( such as Northern China and Japan ) , and the Health Bureau calls for early vaccination of the elderly , children , pregnant women , obese and chronically ill , who are at greater risk of post @-@ flu complications , as well as those who are in regular contact with high @-@ risk populations .
