Domestic oil prices have been pegged to international oil prices . Since the current price cycle , international oil prices have fluctuated , and Brent &apos;s crude oil has continued to climb beyond the $ 80 mark .
As at closing on 28 September , the United States WTI crude oil futures had risen by $ 1.13 and were reported at $ 73.25 per barrel .
Brent crude oil futures increased by $ 1.0 , reporting $ 82.72 per barrel .
Looking at the international situation , tensions such as the United States sanctions against Iran and the overall trend in oil prices were high . Subsequently , the OPEC production cut conference explicitly refused to increase production , gave market confidence , and steadily increased oil prices .
Zhuo Xian , an information @-@ based oil analyst , just said .
