Opening of the 69th International Astronautical Congress in Germany @ - @ CNN
inhua News Agency , Bremen , Germany , October 1 ( Reporter : Ren Yirong Zhang ) - The 69th International Astronautical Congress opened its curtain on October 1 at Bremen Convention Center in Germany , attended by more than 6,300 astronauts , representatives of space agencies and businesses , expert scholars and young students from all over the world .
In his opening statement , the President of the International Astronautical Federation , Jean @-@ Yves Logar , said that the global space enterprise was no longer involving only a handful of countries and institutions and that the number of participants in the year had increased significantly from the previous one , indicating that a growing number of institutions and people were joining .
He called on States to strengthen cooperation and innovation in order to jointly advance the cause of space .
Zhang Kehong , Vice Minister of Industry and Information Technology of China and Director of the National Space Administration , presented China &apos;s space programme at the exchange event and said that China would expand international cooperation in the space field and contribute to the cause of space for humanity .
Representatives of relevant institutions , such as the China Space Science and Technology Consortium and the China Aerospace Science and Technology Industry Corporation , as well as a number of private enterprises , attended and presented the latest achievements of Chinese space , including various launch vehicles , satellites and space science and technology applications products .
The International Astronautical Congress , which has been held annually since 1950 , is the largest gathering of the world &apos;s aviation community .
The Congress lasted five days and was co @-@ sponsored by the International Astronautical Federation , the International Academy of Astronautics , the Center for Applied Technology and Microgravity Studies of Bremen University , the International Institute of Space Law and others .
BEIJING , November 5 - According to a press release released by the China Foreign Trade Center on Sunday , the Canton Fair shows that China &apos;s foreign trade situation remains complex and serious , with 80.6 % of enterprises expecting to export better than the previous year or even in 2018 .
But , given the external environment of rising costs of domestic raw materials , labor , and other factors , and greater trade friction between China and the US , participating firms also believe that next year &apos;s export situation is not promising .
At the closing press conference of the 124th Canton Fair , Xu Bing , deputy secretary @-@ general of the Canton Fair , press spokesman and deputy director of the China Foreign Trade Center , said that the number of overseas purchasers attending the Canton Fair and the number of overseas purchasers entering the conference had all dropped slightly from year to year .
The number of current purchasers attending the conference was 189,812 from 215 countries and territories , a decrease of 1.11 per cent year on year .
Export transactions amounted to RMB 206,494 million ( equivalent to $ 29.86 billion ) , a decrease of 1 per cent from the previous year .
In terms of markets , the BRICS countries increased by 74.4 per cent , 11.4 per cent , 7.2 per cent and 2.5 per cent , respectively , for Japan , the ASEAN 10 countries , the BRICS countries and South Korea , and fell by 30.3 per cent , 8.9 per cent , 7.3 per cent and 0.8 per cent , respectively , for traditional markets such as the United States , Australia , Canada and the European Union .
In terms of industry , transport , mechanical equipment , construction and decorative materials , consumer electronics and information products , and bathroom equipment increased by 24.8 per cent , 21.1 per cent , 20.0 per cent , 15.1 per cent and 7.6 per cent , respectively , while textile clothing and household appliances decreased by 13.0 per cent and 6.7 per cent , respectively .
Xu Bing said that , as a barometer and a sign of the direction of China &apos;s foreign trade , the current Canton Fair procurement situation and data on export transactions show that China &apos;s foreign trade development still faces many uncertainties next year .
However , with the deepening of supply @-@ side structural reforms and the recent introduction of national and local policy measures such as the six stabilization measures , China &apos;s new momentum in foreign trade development is accelerating its accumulation and new developments in the diversification of its corporate market are all important foundations and powerful conditions for the development of foreign trade .
Combining factors from all sides , it is expected that China &apos;s foreign trade exports and imports will continue to grow steadily throughout the year , further improving quality and effectiveness . According to Xu Bing .
According to the China Customs Administration , exports grew by 14.5 per cent year on year in September in United States dollars , imports grew by 14.3 per cent year on year , and the trade surplus in September was $ 31.69 billion , the highest rate of export growth and trade surplus since February this year .
Despite the escalating trade friction between China and the US , China &apos;s export performance in September has greatly surpassed expectations . Foreign demand is strong , firms are grabbing exports before imposing tariffs on the US and overshooting the renminbi exchange rate to depreciate , or major support factors have shown some resilience in China &apos;s foreign trade . However , the impact of the Sino @-@ US trade war on confidence and the impact on the industrial chain should not be underestimated . Analysts believe that China &apos;s foreign trade challenges are likely to manifest themselves in the fourth quarter or next year .
The Reuters survey showed that US fund managers recommended increased cash holdings in September and continued to be cautious , as the United States and China began the latest round of reciprocal import tariffs and the dispute showed no sign of détente .
However , 12 fund managers participating in the survey recommended that North America &apos;s asset allocation increase to its highest level since June 2017 , while the positions of the United Kingdom , the euro area and , in particular , emerging markets declined .
The global equities allocation averaged 56.6 % , with bonds accounting for 35.5 % , largely consistent with last month &apos;s survey .
The most notable change was the increase in the cash @-@ allocation ratio to 5.1 per cent , the highest level since December 2014 .
A fund manager of a large foundation company said that some economic data had brought confidence to the market , but the trade war was still the biggest concern , so it would be better to prepare to enter when the market fell back .
But in September , fund managers preferred stocks , especially in the United States , even if they were perceived as high .
Today , in Shanghai , China &apos;s open landmark , the world &apos;s first major national @-@ level exhibition with import as its theme -- the China International Import Expo -- officially opened its curtain in the expectation of the masses .
An exhibition is like a window of opportunity that gives the world a better understanding of a city and a country .
Through entering this window of the Expo , people see a move toward a higher level of opening up China ; through entering the window of the Expo , people welcome the mutual benefit of the world and China , which reforms and opens up before leaving China .
For a country , openness , like turning into a butterfly , will be painful for a while , but will be replaced by a new one .
General Secretary Xi Jinping &apos;s summary of the road to openness points to an important reason why China can withstand it .
Looking back at the 40 years of reform and opening @-@ up , China , which dared to jump into the sea of world markets , despite its vortex and winds , has always faced all risk challenges in an open @-@ minded manner , continuously unleashing its endogenous momentum and continuously improving its competitiveness .
It can be said that China has used its own real achievements to strongly explain the value and significance of openness .
From a new historical starting point , the organization of the import @-@ focused Expo was a major decision by the Party Central Committee , with Comrade Xi Jinping at its core , to push for a new round of high @-@ level opening to the world . It was a major move by China to open its markets to the world . It was a practical move by China in support of economic globalization and trade liberalization . It demonstrated that the door to opening up China will not be closed , but will only go beyond it with a strong and clear will .
And the strong registration of exhibitors from all over the world and the difficulty in obtaining a showroom are the biggest certainty and best response to China &apos;s broader , broader , and deeper development of an open economy .
More important , the current global economic and trade order has reached a crossroads .
The wall of trade protectionism and the retreat of some countries to the old path of unilateralism have increased the international community &apos;s concerns about the prospects for free trade and added to the uncertainties of a buoyant world economy .
Against this background of times , this grand gathering on the Yellow Pu River reflects China &apos;s defense of free trade , allowing the world to see open markets , shared future Chinese self @-@ confidence , and China assuming responsibility .
Doing it alone is fast , and the public is far away .
By opening its mind and embracing the world , China has not only forcefully promoted its own development , but has also brought huge opportunities to China in various countries and regions of the world .
In recent years , China has provided a range of international public goods , offering real export markets , development opportunities and employment opportunities , and allowing enterprises from all countries to take the China Development Express to waste .
The Expo is also such a public good , a major platform for global economic and trade cooperation .
On top of this platform , more than 3,000 enterprises from more than 130 countries and regions took a new step in the Chinese market with their unique and high @-@ quality products and services .
