According to the Authority &apos;s latest data , in July 2018 @ - @ September , the foreign exchange fund recorded investment income of HK $ 1.6 billion , which is significantly lower than the HK $ 61.8 billion recorded in the same period last year , but better than the revised HK $ 100 million in the second quarter of this year .
n the Legislative Council , Kim Delin , Managing Director of the China @-@ US trade war , said that at the beginning of the Sino @-@ US trade war , the Hong Kong and emerging market stock indices ran counter to the US equity index . Until the end of September and early October , after the US stock market index peaked , market sentiment began to reverse , as investors gradually realized that the trade war was also bad for the US itself .
A change in market sentiment is a good thing , and if trade wars have only one @-@ sided effects , they will do little to resolve matters .
At the same time , however , he pointed out that financial @-@ market volatility would continue to rise if the Sino @-@ US trade war was not resolved .
In the third quarter of this year , the foreign exchange fund &apos;s equity investment losses in Hong Kong narrowed from HK $ 8 to HK $ 4.7 billion compared to the previous quarter , while overseas equity investment returns soared from HK $ 172 to HK $ 12.8 billion ; foreign exchange losses of HK $ 16.2 billion , bond yields of HK $ 9.7 billion , decreased by 24 per cent and 31 per cent , respectively , each quarter , mainly reflecting the general rise in the value of the United States dollar against major currencies during the quarter and the rise in the United States breeding rate from 3 per cent in mid @-@ September .
Foreign exchange funds are used primarily to support the Hong Kong dollar .
Hong Kong has had a Hong Kong dollar @-@ dollar peg exchange rate since 1983 .
Regarding the current financial situation in Hong Kong , Chen Delin said that economic and asset market uncertainty had increased , and downside risks had increased , but Hong Kong &apos;s financial system was robust , defensive , and resilient to earthquakes .
Hong Kong &apos;s international investment position is plentiful , with $ 1.4 trillion in net foreign assets equivalent to four times GDP , 2.5 times higher than Singapore &apos;s and 0.6 times higher than Japan &apos;s , more than enough to cope with downturns or reversals .
Recently , the Hong Kong dollar has continued to fall back and the spreads with the US dollar have widened . Chen Delin pointed out that the exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar rose by more than 400 basis points on September 21 . The market is generally believed to be mainly related to the rise in the Hong Kong dollar &apos;s interest rate . Afterwards , the Hong Kong dollar hovers against the US dollar at a level near 7.80 @ - @ 7.84 . In the near future , the Hong Kong dollar &apos;s interest rate has continued to fall . The spreads with the US dollar have widened . This may attract more interest @-@ rate arbitrage in the market to sell the Hong Kong dollar and buy the US dollar , making it more likely that the Hong Kong dollar will once again trigger the weak party &apos;s guarantee of exchange than in the previous period .
But he believes that as the interest @-@ rate hike cycle of Hong Kong &apos;s banks begins and the Hong Kong dollar interest rate normalizes , the future situation of the Hong Kong dollar interest rate below the dollar rate will change .
The interest rate on the Hong Kong dollar will move more in line with the trend in the United States dollar , and we must be more careful to manage risks and prepare for market volatility .
Due to the abundance of funds in the Hong Kong dollar , the Hong Kong dollar depreciated further , with three @-@ month deduction rates falling by 0.9 to 2.08179 per cent on Monday , the difference with the United States dollar expanding from 46 basis points to 51 basis points , and one @-@ month deduction rates reaching a new low of five months , with the difference with the United States dollar increasing from 120 basis points to 127 basis points .
The spot exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar was close to 7.85 to the United States dollar for most of the period from May to mid @-@ September .
During this period , the weak party exchange assurances were repeatedly activated in May and August , following the first trigger in April , as a result of , inter alia , hedging activities and the release from the Hong Kong dollar of some of the funds obtained after the completion of the large @-@ scale bidding exercise .
The Authority buys the Hong Kong dollar at 7.85 level and buys the United States dollar in accordance with the exchange rate regime in order to maintain stability in the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate .
The Authority purchased approximately HK $ 52.1 billion in May and August under the weak exchange guarantee mechanism .
