Xinhua International Current Situation Review : Defending Multilateralism , China knows one thing .
In the face of the backlash of unilateralism , international rules and the multilateral order are under attack .
To some extent , the confrontation between unilateralism and multilateralism has entered a critical period .
As a responsible power , China joins the international community in upholding multilateralism and promoting it .
Faced with the new challenges of the new situation , China has made a loud voice on the direction and path of multilateralism .
As State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said in his address to the general debate at the 73rd session of the United Nations General Assembly , multilateralism in the new era should adhere to the goal of a win @-@ win cooperation , based on the rule of law , based on fairness and justice , and guided by effective action .
At the same time , China called for the establishment of a global development cooperation framework , with the United Nations at its core and North @-@ South cooperation as the main channel , complemented by South @-@ South cooperation , and called on all parties to work together to build a community of human destinies .
China &apos;s reflections and voices reflect the mainstream voice of the international community .
As Espinosa , President of the General Assembly at its seventy @-@ third session , said , in the current situation , the United Nations needs more than ever to promote multilateralism and preserve a rules @-@ based international system .
The Managing Director of IMF , Lagarde , said that the international community should remain steadfast in upholding the multilateral trading system , upholding international trade rules and resolving differences through consultation .
In recent years , the adjustment of the global economic @-@ political balance of power has been accompanied by the rise of a number of emerging markets and groups of developing countries to play a greater role in the major international multilateral mechanisms , giving new impetus to counter @-@ winding multilateralism .
Looking at this dimension , the concept of multilateralism advocated by China to build a family instead of a small circle , and to adhere to the idea of building together rather than winner @-@ take @-@ all , in keeping with the trend of the times , is the inevitable choice to tackle global challenges and solve the world &apos;s troubles , representing the common aspirations of most countries in the world .
There are advanced ideas and more solid actions .
China &apos;s &quot; one belt , one road &quot; initiative has become the largest platform for international cooperation .
China &apos;s joint international and regional cooperation initiatives , such as the building of the &quot; one belt , one road , one road , one infrastructure investment bank , one 16 + 1 cooperation , &quot; promote international regional cooperation , improve complementarities with existing international systems and order , bring new vitality to multilateral cooperation and contribute to the promotion of a more just and equitable international order .
As a defender of the international order and a practitioner of multilateralism , China is acting increasingly forcefully in the multilateral arena of the United Nations .
Good offices on international hot spots , addressing climate change , participating in peacekeeping operations , contributing to poverty reduction and assisting other countries in implementing the 2030 sustainable development agenda .
As United Nations Secretary @-@ General Guterres said , China has become an important pillar of multilateralism .
As the mistrust deficit facing the world widens , and as populism and polarization rise , so does the world &apos;s need for multilateral cooperation .
At this historic juncture , the international community needs to work together to translate consensus into action , resolutely defend multilateralism and work together to build a community of human destinies .
