The Ministry of Finance piloted a VAT exemption for cross @-@ border electricians
The notification indicated that a policy of tax exemption on value added tax and excise duty was being piloted for exports of goods to e @-@ commerce exporting enterprises in the Comprehensive Test Zone that had not obtained valid certificates of entry and that met the relevant conditions .
( i ) E @-@ commerce exporting enterprises are registered in the Comprehensive Test Zone and on the Integrated Service Platform ( ISP ) at the place of registration for cross @-@ border e @-@ commerce , the date of export , the name of the goods , the unit of measure , the quantity , the unit price and the amount .
( ii ) Export of goods through customs at the site of the Comprehensive Test Zone for the processing of electronic commerce export declarations .
( iii ) Exports of goods that do not fall within the purview of the Ministry of Finance and the Directorate General of Taxes , in accordance with the decision of the State Council , expressly eliminate export rebates ( exemptions ) .
The notification is known to have been in force since 1 October 2018 , whichever is the export date indicated in the Export Commodity Declaration List .
Fifth Voice Month of Disabled Persons Comes to Focus on Sex Education for Disabled Adolescents @ - @ CNN
The topic of sex education for young people in China has been widely discussed in recent years , but the challenges to sex education for young people with disabilities remain daunting .
Recently , a seminar on the challenges and practical strategies of comprehensive sexuality education for persons with disabilities was held in Beijing .
How to educate disabled children and young people about sexuality is an important topic of this seminar .
The Report on Sex @-@ Related Knowledge , Attitudes and Behaviour of Disabled Children and Youth in China , released at the Conference , showed that the proportion of disabled children suffering sexual harassment and abuse was higher than that of healthy children .
More attention is also being paid to sexual protection of handicapped children and adolescents in society .
The purpose of the seminar was to explore ways to promote comprehensive sexuality education for handicapped children and adolescents in China in terms of family support , school education and institutional services , and to support handicapped children and adolescents at the source so that they could enjoy their right to love like others .
Experts believe that public awareness of the handicapped in Chinese society has remained low .
China &apos;s comprehensive sexuality education for persons with disabilities , especially disabled children and adolescents , was not deep enough , owing to such factors as traditional attitudes .
However , in recent years , with the support of the United Nations Educational , Scientific and Cultural Organization ( UNESCO ) and public figures , there have been encouraging developments in sexual and reproductive health education practices and pathways for the full development of persons with disabilities throughout their life cycle .
The Report shows that children and young people with visual , hearing , intellectual and physical disabilities are generally more likely to experience difficulties in acquiring sexual knowledge and understanding intimate relationships than the general population , but are generally more accessible and productive .
A seminar on the challenges and practical strategies of comprehensive sexuality education for persons with disabilities was organized by the Shanghai Public Interest Foundation , with the support of the UNESCO representative office in China , the International Alliance for Persons with Disabilities ( France ) representative office in Beijing and the UNFPA representative office in China , with a view to developing a comprehensive life @-@ cycle approach to sexual and reproductive health education for persons with disabilities in the context of a broader strategy for healthy China ; promoting awareness of international policies on comprehensive sexuality education and the right to health of children and youth with disabilities among policymakers , educators , researchers , social service organizations , parents &apos; representatives and other stakeholders in the field of special education and inclusion ; and conducting a broad exchange of practices , strategies , challenges and resources on sexuality education for children and youth with disabilities in China , with a view to discussing and developing a blueprint for comprehensive sexuality education for children and youth with disabilities in the future and forming a support network .
BEIJING , September 30 - The Central Bank of China released scheduled short @-@ term net outflows of foreign currency assets on Sunday . As of the end of August this year , the central bank &apos;s foreign currency position on forward contracts and futures contracts was zero for 12 consecutive months , and there was still no position in the month .
According to previous central bank data , by the end of August last year , the central bank held a total of $ 6.044 billion in foreign currency positions on forward contracts and futures contracts , the fourth consecutive month , and a total of $ 4.276 billion in empty positions on SDR ( Special Drawing Rights ) .
Since then , the central bank &apos;s foreign @-@ exchange forward position has been zero .
The central bank released the data for the first time at the end of March 2016 ; the data showed that , at the end of February 2016 , the central bank &apos;s foreign currency had an excess position of $ 2,438 million on local currency forward contracts and futures contracts , and an empty position of $ 28.9 billion .
For the first time , September data released at the end of October of the same year showed a net increase of $ 16,401 million to $ 45.301 billion .
The central bank has previously indicated that the forward and forward positions of the foreign currency vis @-@ à @-@ vis the local currency mainly reflect the foreign exchange forward operations undertaken by the central bank with commercial banks to meet the hedging needs of firms &apos; foreign currency liabilities , which will continue to provide forward risk @-@ averse products on a demand @-@ side basis , with the central bank &apos;s forward operations having less impact on the size of future reserves .
