In recent years , this Newspaper ( trainee journalist Li Qiyao ) has experienced numerous incidents of substandard plastic runways on campus .
To this end , the Ministry of Education issued a circular requiring the implementation of the new national standard for the facial stadium of composite materials for primary and secondary schools to be delivered for use after 1 November this year .
The mandatory national standard , the Facebook for Composite Materials in Primary and Secondary Schools , was drafted by the Ministry of Education with the participation of 26 scientific institutions and inspection agencies and was revised more than two years ago , during which more than 100 expert meetings were organized to validate it , as well as field trips and sample inspections throughout the country , collecting numerous validation experiments of hundreds of enterprises &apos; products on the market .
ccording to the old national standard in 2005 , the reporter found that the new national standard not only changed from the recommended national standard to the mandatory national standard , but also added a number of elements , including thickness requirements , physical properties , resistance to aging , inorganic filler content requirements , anti @-@ slippery colloidal polymer content requirements , cap on finished surface harmful substances , limit on non @-@ solid and solid raw materials , etc .
In particular , the new national standard defines the possible harmful substances arising from the construction of the campus &apos;s plastic runway , increasing from 7 to 18 , and sets limits on the amount of volatile organic matter in the completed runway in accordance with home @-@ loading standards .
If the limits and odor requirements for the release of hazardous substances are specified in the ram and preform finished products , the total volatile organic compound should not be greater than 5 mg / m3 , formaldehyde should not be greater than 0.4 mg / m3 , carbon disulfide should not be greater than 7 mg / m3 , benzene should not be greater than 0.1 mg / m3 , and the odor grade should not be higher than 3 .
The new national standard also contains detailed regulations on sampling requirements for plastic runways on primary and secondary school campuses , inspection rules , rules of adjudication , etc .
In addition , the campus artificial lawn was for the first time included in the mandatory national standard testing .
Recently , special work will be carried out on the implementation of the new national standard , and the implementation of the new national standard will be reported to the Sports Health and Arts Education Department of the Ministry of Education in the course of the year .
