Activating rural consumption depends on normalized mechanisms to clean up markets , guide demand for healthy consumption , and improve farmers &apos; sense of access to consumption .
The data show that the consumption potential of the rural population has been steadily unleashed , with retail sales of rural consumer goods growing by 10.5 per cent in the first half of this year , 1.3 percentage points faster than in towns .
In a poor village in a western county , there is only one convenience store in the entire village . It walks into the store . Some commodities seem to know each other . They are labeled &quot; golden dragon oil drops , &quot; and &quot; wangchui drops &quot; become &quot; wangchui drops , &quot; and there are a lot of commodities .
Over the years , similar phenomena have frequently come to light , and some fake and inferior goods in rural areas have become famous , with similar names , similar packaging , and fake truths , making them indefensible .
A consumption survey report released by a western municipality showed that the problem of excessive counterfeit goods in rural areas was serious , with 66 per cent of users buying counterfeit goods in suburban supermarkets , more than half of which were food products .
The relevant departments regulate the rural market and call for attacks every year . Why are Li Dynasty still repeatedly fighting ?
Unlike in urban markets , the relatively low awareness of the rights of peasants , coupled with the remoteness of many rural areas and the fact that they are in blind areas with insufficient regulatory power , give fertile ground to fake and inferior goods .
A commodity with a large number of controls , some departments with prices , some with production , some with markets , some with overlapping functions , annual fake control , centralized control for a while , counterfeit goods escaped the wind and gradually emerged , just finished old holidays , and new ones emerged again .
The lack of long @-@ term regulatory mechanisms , the difficulty of cleaning up the rural market , the low cost of violating the law and the high interest in it have caused some illegal traders to rise to the top of their heads and become squandering the market in some rural areas .
From subsistence to well @-@ being , the vast majority of farmers are moving towards developmental consumption .
Recently , the Party Central Committee and the State Council issued &quot; Several Opinions on Improving the Mechanism for Promoting Consumption and Further Stimulating the Consumer Potential of Residents , &quot; in which they proposed to promote the upgrading of the consumption ladder of rural residents , with the aim of allowing the vast majority of peasants to consume the consumerism of consumering to consume the consumerism of consumerism and allowing rural consumption to truly flourish .
On the one hand , we need to deepen reform , eliminate the many political and administrative shortcomings of market supervision , adapt to local conditions , improve food safety and product quality monitoring networks , and continuously reduce the space for fake and fake sales in rural areas .
On the other hand , we must step up law enforcement efforts , open up supervision and control of indecent blood vessels , and absolutely not allow fake and sham to breed and spread in rural areas .
Rigorous punishment of pit farmers is the only way to protect farmers . No matter how hidden the counterfeiters may be , it should not become a reason for counterfeit goods to breed . The relevant departments should clearly define their responsibilities . Grassroots supervision is weak . Whichever link goes wrong , they should be held accountable and those who make counterfeits or sell them should be left without shelter .
