To create a clean and comfortable market environment for the countryside , so that peasant consumption is not worried , rural consumption can only become more and more robust , and only then can peasant consumption gain a sense of happiness and happiness .
With effect from November 1 , our country will reduce most @-@ favoured @-@ nation ( MFN ) tariffs on some commodities , and the total tariff level will fall to 7.5 %
In accordance with the decision of the twenty @-@ sixth regular session of the State Council , the State Council Committee on Tariff Rules issued a proclamation on 30 November 2018 to reduce most @-@ favoured @-@ nation ( MFN ) rates on selected commodities , effective 1 November 2018 .
According to the Proclamation of the State Council Committee on Tariffs and Duties on the Reduction of Tariffs on Imports of Selected Commodities , the MFN rate for some goods , including industrial products , has been reduced since 1 November of this year in order to accommodate industrial upgrading , lower enterprise costs and meet the needs of the masses for multi @-@ level consumption .
Tax deductions for commodities totalled 1,585 items , representing approximately 19 per cent of the total number of items in our country , and the average tax rate dropped from 10.5 per cent to 7.8 per cent , representing an average reduction of 26 per cent .
This tax reduction relates mainly to textiles ; stones , ceramics , glass products ; some steel and base metal products ; electromechanical equipment and parts thereof , such as metal processing machines , textile machines , engineering machinery , transmission equipment , electrical appliances , instrumentation , etc . ; and resource commodities and primary processing products , such as non @-@ metallic minerals , inorganic chemicals , timber and paper products , and precious stones .
At the same time , as the overall level of tariffs , particularly on medicines and consumer goods , has been lowered , the tariff line rate on import duties on goods entering the country has been reduced accordingly .
In order to implement the decision @-@ making and deployment of the Party Central Committee and the State Council , China has implemented zero tariffs on the vast majority of imported medicines since May 1 of this year , reduced import tariffs on cars and spare parts and some consumer products for daily use from July 1 , and implemented the third step of the information technology agreement to expand the containment products .
The reporter learned from the State Council &apos;s Customs Regulations Committee that since this year , after several successive autonomous adjustments , our country &apos;s total tariff level will fall from 9.8 % last year to 7.5 % , with an average reduction of 23 % .
Appropriate tariff reductions would facilitate the balanced development of external trade and promote higher levels of external openness , as well as the integrated use of both domestic and international resources and the promotion of domestic supply @-@ side structural reforms .
Relevant officials of the committee said that this year marks the fortieth anniversary of reform and opening @-@ up . The initiative to lower the overall level of tariffs is a practical move to implement the spirit of General Secretary Xi Jinping &apos;s important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia . It is also an important move for China to further expand its openness and expand its imports in accordance with its high @-@ quality development needs . This move and initiative shows that China will firmly pursue a mutually beneficial and win @-@ win opening strategy , while enhancing its own development momentum , it will also allow China &apos;s development to better benefit the world .
On September 29 , a regional public brand launch on agricultural products was held in Nankai district , Tianjin city .
The Red Army &apos;s little rice , black beans , mountain children &apos;s songs , Montenegrin sheep , cramped tea , paper @-@ cut skin sheets , pure hand @-@ dragged shoes , and a well @-@ packaged piece of agricultural products were put on the stand , all of which had a common brand name called &quot; crambling . &quot;
Constructing a regional brand name to effectively address the many scattered , small and weak agricultural products in Ring County , the development bottleneck has become a powerful vehicle to fight poverty . On the 29th , a regional public brand launch on agricultural products hosted by Gansu Ring County was held in Nankai district , Tianjin City .
Ring county is located on the border of the three provinces of Shaanxan and Nanning , and has a long history and abundant resources as a hometown where China &apos;s small grains are piled up in Shenzhen County , Shenzhen County .
Snacks such as lamb meat , yellow rice , chopped faces , and softness on oats are all the more often remembered by guerrillas in their homelands .
As the level of urbanization in China continues to rise and the urban population grows rapidly , a large number of young people in rural areas leave their homelands to start urban life .
Yang Xiao Jia , an expert on Chinese agricultural brands , said : &quot; Now that the rhythm of urban life is fast and the pressure is high , more and more people are beginning to miss rural life when they are young , but what they cannot go back is called their hometown . The most beautiful memory is that of the countryside , the countryside , the countryside , the countryside , the countryside , the countryside . The brand design is named after the countryside sentiment and anxiety of the people of the overseas drifting ring county .
The weather conditions in Ring County are exceptional , with long daylight hours , high 24 / 7 temperature differentials , and unique conditions for the cultivation of small grains .
The country produces more than 20 kinds of small grocery grains . It is the country of small grocery grains in China . Its production is the highest in Gansu and its quality is the highest in the country .
Wang Xiaoli was a girl from Ring County who was attending school in Tianjin . She participated in the promotion meeting as a volunteer this time . She said : those who had gone home were the closest , those from the hometown were the most delighted , those from the hometown were the most delighted , and those from the hometown were the most delighted , those from the hometown were the apos . The brand name snapped too many of our countryside worries and memories . What we thought about was even more beautiful food from that time . I hope that those from the hometown would go to the apos . She hoped that the brand would go farther away and grow bigger .
Dr. Tan Bin , researcher at the Scientific Research Institute of the National Food and Material Reserves Bureau , said that by testing more than 900 sets of indicator data , all kinds of testing data on agricultural products such as bucks , bitterness , black beans and other products in Ring County are superior . Many of the physiologically active substances in grocery grains are higher than standard data , and the people in the Ring Village have an inherent advantage in grabbing the high @-@ end grocery market in the country .
Yi Chun @-@ chun , secretary of the Ring county committee , said that by grabbing the brands and publishing them , he can further improve the quality , standardization , and scale @-@ up level of innovative development of high @-@ quality agricultural products in Ring county , and help shape a good overall image of agricultural products in Ring county , rapidly improving visibility , competitiveness , and added value .
Canada &apos;s gross domestic product ( GDP ) grew by 0.2 per cent in July compared to the previous month , a higher @-@ than @-@ expected increase that raised the market &apos;s expectations of interest rate hikes by the Central Bank of Canada next month .
If it does , it will be the central bank &apos;s fifth rate hike in a little more than a year .
Analysts from Reuters &apos;s visit had previously predicted growth of 0.1 % .
Statistics Canada said on Friday that 12 out of 20 industries are growing .
The data are noteworthy because the central bank predicted earlier this month that temporary factors could drag down third @-@ quarter GDP data .
Central Bank of Canada Governor Boroz promised on Thursday that the central bank would continue to raise interest rates gradually , and that it would pay close attention to economic data .
The Bank of Canada &apos;s next interest @-@ rate decision will be announced on October 24 .
With the Canadian economy strengthening and unemployment approaching record lows , the Central Bank of Canada has raised interest rates four times since July 2017 .
According to Stephen Brown , a senior Canadian economist who has invested in macroeconomics , the economy &apos;s third @-@ quarter GDP growth rate is likely to be around 2 % per annum .
This would be higher than the CBC &apos;s forecast of 1.5 % , making it another reason to expect the CBC to raise interest rates next month , as he put it in a report .
The overnight index swap showed that market forecasts of the CBC &apos;s rate hike rate in October had risen from 76.46 per cent to 78.27 per cent .
For the first time in 65 years , South Korea and North Korea jointly visited Han Jiang &apos;s entrance to the sea
South Korea &apos;s Defense Ministry confirmed on the 5th that South Korea and North Korea launched a joint inspection of the waters of the entrance of the Han River and the Linjin River to the sea on the same day .
The initiative is a preliminary preparation to guarantee the free navigation of civilian vessels on both sides .
The South Korean Ministry of Defense &apos;s briefing to the media on the same day showed that this was the first time since the signing of the Korean War Armistice Agreement in 1953 that the two sides had conducted a joint inspection of Han Jiang &apos;s access to the sea .
n September this year , South Korea and North Korea signed a military agreement and agreed to jointly inspect the waters such as the entrance to the sea mouth of the Han River starting in November in order to safeguard the protection of the environment and develop tourism in the waters in the future .
In October , South Korea planned a joint inspection of the waters during a general @-@ military conference .
On November 5 , the joint inspection of the waters of South Korea and North Korea officially began .
The joint mission comprised 20 members of the South Korean military , experts and others .
According to the South Korean Ministry of Defense , during this inspection , neither side &apos;s personnel carried weapons and prohibited the use of words and deeds to stimulate the other side .
Since there is no military demarcation line in the vicinity of the entrance to the sea , the area was an inadvertently high @-@ security zone , but through joint inspection this will become a new peaceful zone in the future .
The waters jointly examined by South Korea and North Korea this time total about 70 kilometers and total about 280 square kilometers .
he South Korean Ministry of Defense said that the South Korean side will send six research boats to investigate the depth of sea waters , etc . , and provide basic information for safe navigation in the waters . Once the investigation is completed , it will provide navigation maps for the movement of civilian vessels .
South Korea held a summit meeting in Pyongyang in October 2007 to reach an agreement on the joint use of the Han and Linzin rivers to access the sea , but subsequent negotiations were stalled by tensions on the peninsula .
According to a military agreement signed by South Korea and North Korea in September , vessels from both sides will need to inform each other in advance before navigating in the common waters .
Chinanews.com , November 5 - According to news from the website of the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia on the 4th , in recent days , Guo Yuqin and Mao Yuxin , Chinese citizens , lost association during the Meng tour .
According to reports , the two men were members of the Blue Sky Rescue Team . On October 19 , they contacted their relatives and friends in the country and said that they were about to enter the mountains near Kusugur Lake and share their location through WeChat . After that , they lost contact and were suspected of having gone to the no @-@ man &apos;s land .
The Chinese Embassy in Mongolia has always attached great importance to the protection of the legitimate rights and security of Chinese citizens in Mongolia and to consular protection and assistance .
Immediately after learning of the missing news from the two tourists , the Embassy launched an emergency plan to take care of the gold rescue time and make every effort to carry out its work .
The Embassy maintains close communication with the family members of the client , assists them in immediately reporting the case to the Mongol police and provides the family with an alternative translation list .
The Embassy first met with the heads of the Ministry of External Relations of Mongolia , the Police Department and the Emergency Department to brief them on the situation , and requested the Mongolian side to carry out search and rescue as soon as possible and to maintain close communication with the Mongolian side throughout the search and rescue process to ensure that it was kept abreast of the latest developments .
At the same time , the embassy assisted the family in publicizing people &apos;s thoughts in Mongolia , and extensively mobilized overseas Mongolian nationals and Chinese @-@ funded enterprises to participate actively in the search for people , providing effective leads , and provided related assistance to a number of Blue Sky rescue workers who went to Mongolia to assist in the rescue .
Under the strong impetus of the Embassy , the Mongolian side dispatched rescue teams for the first time and promised to waive search and rescue fees .
The Directorate @-@ General of Police and the Directorate @-@ General of Emergency Situations have instructed the police and emergency departments of the province of Kousugur to make every effort to search and rescue them .
Because Lake Kusukur is situated on the northern border of Mongolia with Russia , is remote , sparsely populated and extremely inaccessible in terms of traffic and communications , and Mongolia has now entered a harsh winter , with temperatures as low as about 20 degrees below zero , the local police and emergency departments have overcome enormous difficulties , mobilizing almost all police forces and mobilizing local herders to carry out extensive carpet search and rescue around their disconnected positions for days through horse riding , walking and visiting herders .
At the same time , in response to the peculiar situation in the pastoral areas , the Mongolian side has been circulating thought @-@ provoking messages through the radio cycle for many days .
n China , relevant workers of the Blue Sky Rescue Team have come to Mongolia to participate actively in the rescue together with the Mongolian side .
The safety and security of the two disjointed men has always touched our hearts .
So far , more than a decade after their loss , the embassy has received a number of leads , but they have not yet been located , and the search and rescue operations are still under intense strain .
The Embassy will always be guided by the principle of putting people first , keeping the matter under constant review , encouraging the Mongolian side to continue to make every effort to search and rescue and to provide maximum assistance to the families of the persons concerned .
The Embassy called on compatriots and enterprises in Mongolia to contact the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia for the first time if they learned of the relevant leads .
